2582/**
2583 * Return TRUE if the stream has accurate duration in any stream.
2584 *
2585 * @return TRUE if the stream has accurate duration for at least one component.
2586 */
2587static int has_duration(AVFormatContext *ic)
2588{
2589 int i;
2590 AVStream *st;
2591
2592 for (i = 0; i < ic->nb_streams; i++) {
2593 st = ic->streams[i];
2594 if (st->duration != AV_NOPTS_VALUE)
2595 return 1;
2596 }
2597 if (ic->duration != AV_NOPTS_VALUE)
2598 return 1;
2599 return 0;
2600}
2601
2602/**
2603 * Estimate the stream timings from the one of each components.
2604 *
2605 * Also computes the global bitrate if possible.
2606 */
2607static void update_stream_timings(AVFormatContext *ic)
2608{
2609 int64_t start_time, start_time1, start_time_text, end_time, end_time1, end_time_text;
2610 int64_t duration, duration1, duration_text, filesize;
2611 int i;
2612 AVProgram *p;
2613
2614 start_time = INT64_MAX;
2615 start_time_text = INT64_MAX;
2616 end_time = INT64_MIN;
2617 end_time_text = INT64_MIN;
2618 duration = INT64_MIN;
2619 duration_text = INT64_MIN;
2620
2621 for (i = 0; i < ic->nb_streams; i++) {
2622 AVStream *st = ic->streams[i];
2623 int is_text = st->codecpar->codec_type == AVMEDIA_TYPE_SUBTITLE ||
2624 st->codecpar->codec_type == AVMEDIA_TYPE_DATA;
2625 if (st->start_time != AV_NOPTS_VALUE && st->time_base.den) {
2626 start_time1 = av_rescale_q(st->start_time, st->time_base,
2627 AV_TIME_BASE_Q);
2628 if (is_text)
2629 start_time_text = FFMIN(start_time_text, start_time1);
2630 else
2631 start_time = FFMIN(start_time, start_time1);
2632 end_time1 = av_rescale_q_rnd(st->duration, st->time_base,
2633 AV_TIME_BASE_Q,
2634 AV_ROUND_NEAR_INF|AV_ROUND_PASS_MINMAX);
2635 if (end_time1 != AV_NOPTS_VALUE && (end_time1 > 0 ? start_time1 <= INT64_MAX - end_time1 : start_time1 >= INT64_MIN - end_time1)) {
2636 end_time1 += start_time1;
2637 if (is_text)
2638 end_time_text = FFMAX(end_time_text, end_time1);
2639 else
2640 end_time = FFMAX(end_time, end_time1);
2641 }
2642 for (p = NULL; (p = av_find_program_from_stream(ic, p, i)); ) {
2643 if (p->start_time == AV_NOPTS_VALUE || p->start_time > start_time1)
2644 p->start_time = start_time1;
2645 if (p->end_time < end_time1)
2646 p->end_time = end_time1;
2647 }
2648 }
2649 if (st->duration != AV_NOPTS_VALUE) {
2650 duration1 = av_rescale_q(st->duration, st->time_base,
2651 AV_TIME_BASE_Q);
2652 if (is_text)
2653 duration_text = FFMAX(duration_text, duration1);
2654 else
2655 duration = FFMAX(duration, duration1);
2656 }
2657 }
2658 if (start_time == INT64_MAX || (start_time > start_time_text && start_time - (uint64_t)start_time_text < AV_TIME_BASE))
2659 start_time = start_time_text;
2660 else if (start_time > start_time_text)
2661 av_log(ic, AV_LOG_VERBOSE, "Ignoring outlier non primary stream starttime %f\n", start_time_text / (float)AV_TIME_BASE);
2662
2663 if (end_time == INT64_MIN || (end_time < end_time_text && end_time_text - (uint64_t)end_time < AV_TIME_BASE))
2664 end_time = end_time_text;
2665 else if (end_time < end_time_text)
2666 av_log(ic, AV_LOG_VERBOSE, "Ignoring outlier non primary stream endtime %f\n", end_time_text / (float)AV_TIME_BASE);
2667
2668 if (duration == INT64_MIN || (duration < duration_text && duration_text - duration < AV_TIME_BASE))
2669 duration = duration_text;
2670 else if (duration < duration_text)
2671 av_log(ic, AV_LOG_VERBOSE, "Ignoring outlier non primary stream duration %f\n", duration_text / (float)AV_TIME_BASE);
2672
2673 if (start_time != INT64_MAX) {
2674 ic->start_time = start_time;
2675 if (end_time != INT64_MIN) {
2676 if (ic->nb_programs > 1) {
2677 for (i = 0; i < ic->nb_programs; i++) {
2678 p = ic->programs[i];
2679 if (p->start_time != AV_NOPTS_VALUE &&
2680 p->end_time > p->start_time &&
2681 p->end_time - (uint64_t)p->start_time <= INT64_MAX)
2682 duration = FFMAX(duration, p->end_time - p->start_time);
2683 }
2684 } else if (end_time >= start_time && end_time - (uint64_t)start_time <= INT64_MAX) {
2685 duration = FFMAX(duration, end_time - start_time);
2686 }
2687 }
2688 }
2689 if (duration != INT64_MIN && duration > 0 && ic->duration == AV_NOPTS_VALUE) {
2690 ic->duration = duration;
2691 }
2692 if (ic->pb && (filesize = avio_size(ic->pb)) > 0 && ic->duration > 0) {
2693 /* compute the bitrate */
2694 double bitrate = (double) filesize * 8.0 * AV_TIME_BASE /
2695 (double) ic->duration;
2696 if (bitrate >= 0 && bitrate <= INT64_MAX)
2697 ic->bit_rate = bitrate;
2698 }
2699}
2700
2701static void fill_all_stream_timings(AVFormatContext *ic)
2702{
2703 int i;
2704 AVStream *st;
2705
2706 update_stream_timings(ic);
2707 for (i = 0; i < ic->nb_streams; i++) {
2708 st = ic->streams[i];
2709 if (st->start_time == AV_NOPTS_VALUE) {
2710 if (ic->start_time != AV_NOPTS_VALUE)
2711 st->start_time = av_rescale_q(ic->start_time, AV_TIME_BASE_Q,
2712 st->time_base);
2713 if (ic->duration != AV_NOPTS_VALUE)
2714 st->duration = av_rescale_q(ic->duration, AV_TIME_BASE_Q,
2715 st->time_base);
2716 }
2717 }
2718}
2719
2720static void estimate_timings_from_bit_rate(AVFormatContext *ic)
2721{
2722 int64_t filesize, duration;
2723 int i, show_warning = 0;
2724 AVStream *st;
2725
2726 /* if bit_rate is already set, we believe it */
2727 if (ic->bit_rate <= 0) {
2728 int64_t bit_rate = 0;
2729 for (i = 0; i < ic->nb_streams; i++) {
2730 st = ic->streams[i];
2731 if (st->codecpar->bit_rate <= 0 && st->internal->avctx->bit_rate > 0)
2732 st->codecpar->bit_rate = st->internal->avctx->bit_rate;
2733 if (st->codecpar->bit_rate > 0) {
2734 if (INT64_MAX - st->codecpar->bit_rate < bit_rate) {
2735 bit_rate = 0;
2736 break;
2737 }
2738 bit_rate += st->codecpar->bit_rate;
2739 } else if (st->codecpar->codec_type == AVMEDIA_TYPE_VIDEO && st->codec_info_nb_frames > 1) {
2740 // If we have a videostream with packets but without a bitrate
2741 // then consider the sum not known
2742 bit_rate = 0;
2743 break;
2744 }
2745 }
2746 ic->bit_rate = bit_rate;
2747 }
2748
2749 /* if duration is already set, we believe it */
2750 if (ic->duration == AV_NOPTS_VALUE &&
2751 ic->bit_rate != 0) {
2752 filesize = ic->pb ? avio_size(ic->pb) : 0;
2753 if (filesize > ic->internal->data_offset) {
2754 filesize -= ic->internal->data_offset;
2755 for (i = 0; i < ic->nb_streams; i++) {
2756 st = ic->streams[i];
2757 if ( st->time_base.num <= INT64_MAX / ic->bit_rate
2758 && st->duration == AV_NOPTS_VALUE) {
2759 duration = av_rescale(filesize, 8LL * st->time_base.den,
2760 ic->bit_rate *
2761 (int64_t) st->time_base.num);
2762 st->duration = duration;
2763 show_warning = 1;
2764 }
2765 }
2766 }
2767 }
2768 if (show_warning)
2769 av_log(ic, AV_LOG_WARNING,
2770 "Estimating duration from bitrate, this may be inaccurate\n");
2771}
2772
2773#define DURATION_MAX_READ_SIZE 250000LL
2774#define DURATION_MAX_RETRY 6
2775
2776/* only usable for MPEG-PS streams */
2777static void estimate_timings_from_pts(AVFormatContext *ic, int64_t old_offset)
2778{
2779 AVPacket *pkt = ic->internal->pkt;
2780 AVStream *st;
2781 int num, den, read_size, i, ret;
2782 int found_duration = 0;
2783 int is_end;
2784 int64_t filesize, offset, duration;
2785 int retry = 0;
2786
2787 /* flush packet queue */
2788 flush_packet_queue(ic);
2789
2790 for (i = 0; i < ic->nb_streams; i++) {
2791 st = ic->streams[i];
2792 if (st->start_time == AV_NOPTS_VALUE &&
2793 st->first_dts == AV_NOPTS_VALUE &&
2794 st->codecpar->codec_type != AVMEDIA_TYPE_UNKNOWN)
2795 av_log(ic, AV_LOG_WARNING,
2796 "start time for stream %d is not set in estimate_timings_from_pts\n", i);
2797
2798 if (st->parser) {
2799 av_parser_close(st->parser);
2800 st->parser = NULL;
2801 }
2802 }
2803
2804 if (ic->skip_estimate_duration_from_pts) {
2805 av_log(ic, AV_LOG_INFO, "Skipping duration calculation in estimate_timings_from_pts\n");
2806 goto skip_duration_calc;
2807 }
2808
2809 av_opt_set(ic, "skip_changes", "1", AV_OPT_SEARCH_CHILDREN);
2810 /* estimate the end time (duration) */
2811 /* XXX: may need to support wrapping */
2812 filesize = ic->pb ? avio_size(ic->pb) : 0;
2813 do {
2814 is_end = found_duration;
2815 offset = filesize - (DURATION_MAX_READ_SIZE << retry);
2816 if (offset < 0)
2817 offset = 0;
2818
2819 avio_seek(ic->pb, offset, SEEK_SET);
2820 read_size = 0;
2821 for (;;) {
2822 if (read_size >= DURATION_MAX_READ_SIZE << (FFMAX(retry - 1, 0)))
2823 break;
2824
2825 do {
2826 ret = ff_read_packet(ic, pkt);
2827 } while (ret == AVERROR(EAGAIN));
2828 if (ret != 0)
2829 break;
2830 read_size += pkt->size;
2831 st = ic->streams[pkt->stream_index];
2832 if (pkt->pts != AV_NOPTS_VALUE &&
2833 (st->start_time != AV_NOPTS_VALUE ||
2834 st->first_dts != AV_NOPTS_VALUE)) {
2835 if (pkt->duration == 0) {
2836 ff_compute_frame_duration(ic, &num, &den, st, st->parser, pkt);
2837 if (den && num) {
2838 pkt->duration = av_rescale_rnd(1,
2839 num * (int64_t) st->time_base.den,
2840 den * (int64_t) st->time_base.num,
2841 AV_ROUND_DOWN);
2842 }
2843 }
2844 duration = pkt->pts + pkt->duration;
2845 found_duration = 1;
2846 if (st->start_time != AV_NOPTS_VALUE)
2847 duration -= st->start_time;
2848 else
2849 duration -= st->first_dts;
2850 if (duration > 0) {
2851 if (st->duration == AV_NOPTS_VALUE || st->internal->info->last_duration<= 0 ||
2852 (st->duration < duration && FFABS(duration - st->internal->info->last_duration) < 60LL*st->time_base.den / st->time_base.num))
2853 st->duration = duration;
2854 st->internal->info->last_duration = duration;
2855 }
2856 }
2857 av_packet_unref(pkt);
2858 }
2859
2860 /* check if all audio/video streams have valid duration */
2861 if (!is_end) {
2862 is_end = 1;
2863 for (i = 0; i < ic->nb_streams; i++) {
2864 st = ic->streams[i];
2865 switch (st->codecpar->codec_type) {
2866 case AVMEDIA_TYPE_VIDEO:
2867 case AVMEDIA_TYPE_AUDIO:
2868 if (st->duration == AV_NOPTS_VALUE)
2869 is_end = 0;
2870 }
2871 }
2872 }
2873 } while (!is_end &&
2874 offset &&
2875 ++retry <= DURATION_MAX_RETRY);
2876
2877 av_opt_set(ic, "skip_changes", "0", AV_OPT_SEARCH_CHILDREN);
2878
2879 /* warn about audio/video streams which duration could not be estimated */
2880 for (i = 0; i < ic->nb_streams; i++) {
2881 st = ic->streams[i];
2882 if (st->duration == AV_NOPTS_VALUE) {
2883 switch (st->codecpar->codec_type) {
2884 case AVMEDIA_TYPE_VIDEO:
2885 case AVMEDIA_TYPE_AUDIO:
2886 if (st->start_time != AV_NOPTS_VALUE || st->first_dts != AV_NOPTS_VALUE) {
2887 av_log(ic, AV_LOG_WARNING, "stream %d : no PTS found at end of file, duration not set\n", i);
2888 } else
2889 av_log(ic, AV_LOG_WARNING, "stream %d : no TS found at start of file, duration not set\n", i);
2890 }
2891 }
2892 }
2893skip_duration_calc:
2894 fill_all_stream_timings(ic);
2895
2896 avio_seek(ic->pb, old_offset, SEEK_SET);
2897 for (i = 0; i < ic->nb_streams; i++) {
2898 int j;
2899
2900 st = ic->streams[i];
2901 st->cur_dts = st->first_dts;
2902 st->last_IP_pts = AV_NOPTS_VALUE;
2903 st->internal->last_dts_for_order_check = AV_NOPTS_VALUE;
2904 for (j = 0; j < MAX_REORDER_DELAY + 1; j++)
2905 st->internal->pts_buffer[j] = AV_NOPTS_VALUE;
2906 }
2907}
2908
2909/* 1:1 map to AVDurationEstimationMethod */
2910static const char *const duration_name[] = {
2911 [AVFMT_DURATION_FROM_PTS] = "pts",
2912 [AVFMT_DURATION_FROM_STREAM] = "stream",
2913 [AVFMT_DURATION_FROM_BITRATE] = "bit rate",
2914};

2917{

2919}
2920
2921static void estimate_timings(AVFormatContext *ic, int64_t old_offset)
2922{
2923 int64_t file_size;
2924
2925 /* get the file size, if possible */
2926 if (ic->iformat->flags & AVFMT_NOFILE) {
2927 file_size = 0;
2928 } else {
2929 file_size = avio_size(ic->pb);
2930 file_size = FFMAX(0, file_size);
2931 }
2932
2933 if ((!strcmp(ic->iformat->name, "mpeg") ||
2934 !strcmp(ic->iformat->name, "mpegts")) &&
2935 file_size && (ic->pb->seekable & AVIO_SEEKABLE_NORMAL)) {
2936 /* get accurate estimate from the PTSes */
2937 estimate_timings_from_pts(ic, old_offset);
2938 ic->duration_estimation_method = AVFMT_DURATION_FROM_PTS;
2939 } else if (has_duration(ic)) {
2940 /* at least one component has timings - we use them for all
2941 * the components */
2942 fill_all_stream_timings(ic);
2943 /* nut demuxer estimate the duration from PTS */
2944 if(!strcmp(ic->iformat->name, "nut"))
2945 ic->duration_estimation_method = AVFMT_DURATION_FROM_PTS;
2946 else
2947 ic->duration_estimation_method = AVFMT_DURATION_FROM_STREAM;
2948 } else {
2949 /* less precise: use bitrate info */
2950 estimate_timings_from_bit_rate(ic);
2951 ic->duration_estimation_method = AVFMT_DURATION_FROM_BITRATE;
2952 }
2953 update_stream_timings(ic);
2954
2955 {
2956 int i;
2957 AVStream av_unused *st;
2958 for (i = 0; i < ic->nb_streams; i++) {
2959 st = ic->streams[i];
2960 if (st->time_base.den)
2961 av_log(ic, AV_LOG_TRACE, "stream %d: start_time: %s duration: %s\n", i,
2962 av_ts2timestr(st->start_time, &st->time_base),
2963 av_ts2timestr(st->duration, &st->time_base));
2964 }
2965 av_log(ic, AV_LOG_TRACE,
2966 "format: start_time: %s duration: %s (estimate from %s) bitrate=%"PRId64" kb/s\n",
2967 av_ts2timestr(ic->start_time, &AV_TIME_BASE_Q),
2968 av_ts2timestr(ic->duration, &AV_TIME_BASE_Q),
2969 duration_estimate_name(ic->duration_estimation_method),
2970 (int64_t)ic->bit_rate / 1000);
2971 }
2972}

2974static int has_codec_parameters(AVStream *st, const char **errmsg_ptr)
2975{
2976 AVCodecContext *avctx = st->internal->avctx;
2977
2978#define FAIL(errmsg) do { \
2979 if (errmsg_ptr) \
2980 *errmsg_ptr = errmsg; \
2981 return 0; \
2982 } while (0)
2983
2984 if ( avctx->codec_id == AV_CODEC_ID_NONE
2985 && avctx->codec_type != AVMEDIA_TYPE_DATA)
2986 FAIL("unknown codec");
2987 switch (avctx->codec_type) {
2988 case AVMEDIA_TYPE_AUDIO:
2989 if (!avctx->frame_size && determinable_frame_size(avctx))
2990 FAIL("unspecified frame size");
2991 if (st->internal->info->found_decoder >= 0 &&
2992 avctx->sample_fmt == AV_SAMPLE_FMT_NONE)
2993 FAIL("unspecified sample format");
2994 if (!avctx->sample_rate)
2995 FAIL("unspecified sample rate");
2996 if (!avctx->channels)
2997 FAIL("unspecified number of channels");
2998 if (st->internal->info->found_decoder >= 0 && !st->internal->nb_decoded_frames && avctx->codec_id == AV_CODEC_ID_DTS)
2999 FAIL("no decodable DTS frames");
3000 break;
3001 case AVMEDIA_TYPE_VIDEO:
3002 if (!avctx->width)
3003 FAIL("unspecified size");
3004 if (st->internal->info->found_decoder >= 0 && avctx->pix_fmt == AV_PIX_FMT_NONE)
3005 FAIL("unspecified pixel format");
3006 if (st->codecpar->codec_id == AV_CODEC_ID_RV30 || st->codecpar->codec_id == AV_CODEC_ID_RV40)
3007 if (!st->sample_aspect_ratio.num && !st->codecpar->sample_aspect_ratio.num && !st->codec_info_nb_frames)
3008 FAIL("no frame in rv30/40 and no sar");
3009 break;
3010 case AVMEDIA_TYPE_SUBTITLE:
3011 if (avctx->codec_id == AV_CODEC_ID_HDMV_PGS_SUBTITLE && !avctx->width)
3012 FAIL("unspecified size");
3013 break;
3014 case AVMEDIA_TYPE_DATA:
3015 if (avctx->codec_id == AV_CODEC_ID_NONE) return 1;
3016 }
3017
3018 return 1;
3019}

3021/* returns 1 or 0 if or if not decoded data was returned, or a negative error */
3022static int try_decode_frame(AVFormatContext *s, AVStream *st,
3023 const AVPacket *avpkt, AVDictionary **options)
3024{
3025 AVCodecContext *avctx = st->internal->avctx;
3026 const AVCodec *codec;
3027 int got_picture = 1, ret = 0;
3028 AVFrame *frame = av_frame_alloc();
3029 AVSubtitle subtitle;
3030 AVPacket pkt = *avpkt;
3031 int do_skip_frame = 0;
3032 enum AVDiscard skip_frame;
3033
3034 if (!frame)
3035 return AVERROR(ENOMEM);
3036
3037 if (!avcodec_is_open(avctx) &&
3038 st->internal->info->found_decoder <= 0 &&
3039 (st->codecpar->codec_id != -st->internal->info->found_decoder || !st->codecpar->codec_id)) {
3040 AVDictionary *thread_opt = NULL;
3041
3042 codec = find_probe_decoder(s, st, st->codecpar->codec_id);
3043
3044 if (!codec) {
3045 st->internal->info->found_decoder = -st->codecpar->codec_id;
3046 ret = -1;
3047 goto fail;
3048 }
3049
3050 /* Force thread count to 1 since the H.264 decoder will not extract
3051 * SPS and PPS to extradata during multi-threaded decoding. */
3052 av_dict_set(options ? options : &thread_opt, "threads", "1", 0);
3053 /* Force lowres to 0. The decoder might reduce the video size by the
3054 * lowres factor, and we don't want that propagated to the stream's
3055 * codecpar */
3056 av_dict_set(options ? options : &thread_opt, "lowres", "0", 0);
3057 if (s->codec_whitelist)
3058 av_dict_set(options ? options : &thread_opt, "codec_whitelist", s->codec_whitelist, 0);
3059 ret = avcodec_open2(avctx, codec, options ? options : &thread_opt);
3060 if (!options)
3061 av_dict_free(&thread_opt);
3062 if (ret < 0) {
3063 st->internal->info->found_decoder = -avctx->codec_id;
3064 goto fail;
3065 }
3066 st->internal->info->found_decoder = 1;
3067 } else if (!st->internal->info->found_decoder)
3068 st->internal->info->found_decoder = 1;
3069
3070 if (st->internal->info->found_decoder < 0) {
3071 ret = -1;
3072 goto fail;
3073 }
3074
3075 if (avpriv_codec_get_cap_skip_frame_fill_param(avctx->codec)) {
3076 do_skip_frame = 1;
3077 skip_frame = avctx->skip_frame;
3078 avctx->skip_frame = AVDISCARD_ALL;
3079 }
3080
3081 while ((pkt.size > 0 || (!pkt.data && got_picture)) &&
3082 ret >= 0 &&
3083 (!has_codec_parameters(st, NULL) || !has_decode_delay_been_guessed(st) ||
3084 (!st->codec_info_nb_frames &&
3085 (avctx->codec->capabilities & AV_CODEC_CAP_CHANNEL_CONF)))) {
3086 got_picture = 0;
3087 if (avctx->codec_type == AVMEDIA_TYPE_VIDEO ||
3088 avctx->codec_type == AVMEDIA_TYPE_AUDIO) {
3089 ret = avcodec_send_packet(avctx, &pkt);
3090 if (ret < 0 && ret != AVERROR(EAGAIN) && ret != AVERROR_EOF)
3091 break;
3092 if (ret >= 0)
3093 pkt.size = 0;
3094 ret = avcodec_receive_frame(avctx, frame);
3095 if (ret >= 0)
3096 got_picture = 1;
3097 if (ret == AVERROR(EAGAIN) || ret == AVERROR_EOF)
3098 ret = 0;
3099 } else if (avctx->codec_type == AVMEDIA_TYPE_SUBTITLE) {
3100 ret = avcodec_decode_subtitle2(avctx, &subtitle,
3101 &got_picture, &pkt);
3102 if (got_picture)
3103 avsubtitle_free(&subtitle);
3104 if (ret >= 0)
3105 pkt.size = 0;
3106 }
3107 if (ret >= 0) {
3108 if (got_picture)
3109 st->internal->nb_decoded_frames++;
3110 ret = got_picture;
3111 }
3112 }
3113
3114 if (!pkt.data && !got_picture)
3115 ret = -1;
3116
3117fail:
3118 if (do_skip_frame) {
3119 avctx->skip_frame = skip_frame;
3120 }
3121
3122 av_frame_free(&frame);
3123 return ret;
3124}

3148enum AVCodecID ff_get_pcm_codec_id(int bps, int flt, int be, int sflags)
3149{
3150 if (bps <= 0 || bps > 64)
3151 return AV_CODEC_ID_NONE;
3152
3153 if (flt) {
3154 switch (bps) {
3155 case 32:
3156 return be ? AV_CODEC_ID_PCM_F32BE : AV_CODEC_ID_PCM_F32LE;
3157 case 64:
3158 return be ? AV_CODEC_ID_PCM_F64BE : AV_CODEC_ID_PCM_F64LE;
3159 default:
3160 return AV_CODEC_ID_NONE;
3161 }
3162 } else {
3163 bps += 7;
3164 bps >>= 3;
3165 if (sflags & (1 << (bps - 1))) {
3166 switch (bps) {
3167 case 1:
3168 return AV_CODEC_ID_PCM_S8;
3169 case 2:
3170 return be ? AV_CODEC_ID_PCM_S16BE : AV_CODEC_ID_PCM_S16LE;
3171 case 3:
3172 return be ? AV_CODEC_ID_PCM_S24BE : AV_CODEC_ID_PCM_S24LE;
3173 case 4:
3174 return be ? AV_CODEC_ID_PCM_S32BE : AV_CODEC_ID_PCM_S32LE;
3175 case 8:
3176 return be ? AV_CODEC_ID_PCM_S64BE : AV_CODEC_ID_PCM_S64LE;
3177 default:
3178 return AV_CODEC_ID_NONE;
3179 }
3180 } else {
3181 switch (bps) {
3182 case 1:
3183 return AV_CODEC_ID_PCM_U8;
3184 case 2:
3185 return be ? AV_CODEC_ID_PCM_U16BE : AV_CODEC_ID_PCM_U16LE;
3186 case 3:
3187 return be ? AV_CODEC_ID_PCM_U24BE : AV_CODEC_ID_PCM_U24LE;
3188 case 4:
3189 return be ? AV_CODEC_ID_PCM_U32BE : AV_CODEC_ID_PCM_U32LE;
3190 default:
3191 return AV_CODEC_ID_NONE;
3192 }
3193 }
3194 }
3195}

3233static int chapter_start_cmp(const void *p1, const void *p2)
3234{
3235 AVChapter *ch1 = *(AVChapter**)p1;
3236 AVChapter *ch2 = *(AVChapter**)p2;
3237 int delta = av_compare_ts(ch1->start, ch1->time_base, ch2->start, ch2->time_base);
3238 if (delta)
3239 return delta;
3240 return (ch1 > ch2) - (ch1 < ch2);
3241}
3242
3243static int compute_chapters_end(AVFormatContext *s)
3244{
3245 unsigned int i;
3246 int64_t max_time = 0;
3247 AVChapter **timetable = av_malloc(s->nb_chapters * sizeof(*timetable));
3248
3249 if (!timetable)
3250 return AVERROR(ENOMEM);
3251
3252 if (s->duration > 0 && s->start_time < INT64_MAX - s->duration)
3253 max_time = s->duration +
3254 ((s->start_time == AV_NOPTS_VALUE) ? 0 : s->start_time);
3255
3256 for (i = 0; i < s->nb_chapters; i++)
3257 timetable[i] = s->chapters[i];
3258 qsort(timetable, s->nb_chapters, sizeof(*timetable), chapter_start_cmp);
3259
3260 for (i = 0; i < s->nb_chapters; i++)
3261 if (timetable[i]->end == AV_NOPTS_VALUE) {
3262 AVChapter *ch = timetable[i];
3263 int64_t end = max_time ? av_rescale_q(max_time, AV_TIME_BASE_Q,
3264 ch->time_base)
3265 : INT64_MAX;
3266
3267 if (i + 1 < s->nb_chapters) {
3268 AVChapter *ch1 = timetable[i + 1];
3269 int64_t next_start = av_rescale_q(ch1->start, ch1->time_base,
3270 ch->time_base);
3271 if (next_start > ch->start && next_start < end)
3272 end = next_start;
3273 }
3274 ch->end = (end == INT64_MAX || end < ch->start) ? ch->start : end;
3275 }
3276 av_free(timetable);
3277 return 0;
3278}
3279
3280static int get_std_framerate(int i)
3281{
3282 if (i < 30*12)
3283 return (i + 1) * 1001;
3284 i -= 30*12;
3285
3286 if (i < 30)
3287 return (i + 31) * 1001 * 12;
3288 i -= 30;
3289
3290 if (i < 3)
3291 return ((const int[]) { 80, 120, 240})[i] * 1001 * 12;
3292
3293 i -= 3;
3294
3295 return ((const int[]) { 24, 30, 60, 12, 15, 48 })[i] * 1000 * 12;
3296}

3298/* Is the time base unreliable?
3299 * This is a heuristic to balance between quick acceptance of the values in
3300 * the headers vs. some extra checks.
3301 * Old DivX and Xvid often have nonsense timebases like 1fps or 2fps.
3302 * MPEG-2 commonly misuses field repeat flags to store different framerates.
3303 * And there are "variable" fps files this needs to detect as well. */
3304static int tb_unreliable(AVCodecContext *c)
3305{
3306 if (c->time_base.den >= 101LL * c->time_base.num ||
3307 c->time_base.den < 5LL * c->time_base.num ||
3308 // c->codec_tag == AV_RL32("DIVX") ||
3309 // c->codec_tag == AV_RL32("XVID") ||
3310 c->codec_tag == AV_RL32("mp4v") ||
3311 c->codec_id == AV_CODEC_ID_MPEG2VIDEO ||
3312 c->codec_id == AV_CODEC_ID_GIF ||
3313 c->codec_id == AV_CODEC_ID_HEVC ||
3314 c->codec_id == AV_CODEC_ID_H264)
3315 return 1;
3316 return 0;
3317}

3353int ff_rfps_add_frame(AVFormatContext *ic, AVStream *st, int64_t ts)
3354{
3355 int i, j;
3356 int64_t last = st->internal->info->last_dts;
3357
3358 if ( ts != AV_NOPTS_VALUE && last != AV_NOPTS_VALUE && ts > last
3359 && ts - (uint64_t)last < INT64_MAX) {
3360 double dts = (is_relative(ts) ? ts - RELATIVE_TS_BASE : ts) * av_q2d(st->time_base);
3361 int64_t duration = ts - last;
3362
3363 if (!st->internal->info->duration_error)
3364 st->internal->info->duration_error = av_mallocz(sizeof(st->internal->info->duration_error[0])*2);
3365 if (!st->internal->info->duration_error)
3366 return AVERROR(ENOMEM);
3367
3368// if (st->codec->codec_type == AVMEDIA_TYPE_VIDEO)
3369// av_log(NULL, AV_LOG_ERROR, "%f\n", dts);
3370 for (i = 0; i<MAX_STD_TIMEBASES; i++) {
3371 if (st->internal->info->duration_error[0][1][i] < 1e10) {
3372 int framerate = get_std_framerate(i);
3373 double sdts = dts*framerate/(1001*12);
3374 for (j= 0; j<2; j++) {
3375 int64_t ticks = llrint(sdts+j*0.5);
3376 double error= sdts - ticks + j*0.5;
3377 st->internal->info->duration_error[j][0][i] += error;
3378 st->internal->info->duration_error[j][1][i] += error*error;
3379 }
3380 }
3381 }
3382 if (st->internal->info->rfps_duration_sum <= INT64_MAX - duration) {
3383 st->internal->info->duration_count++;
3384 st->internal->info->rfps_duration_sum += duration;
3385 }
3386
3387 if (st->internal->info->duration_count % 10 == 0) {
3388 int n = st->internal->info->duration_count;
3389 for (i = 0; i<MAX_STD_TIMEBASES; i++) {
3390 if (st->internal->info->duration_error[0][1][i] < 1e10) {
3391 double a0 = st->internal->info->duration_error[0][0][i] / n;
3392 double error0 = st->internal->info->duration_error[0][1][i] / n - a0*a0;
3393 double a1 = st->internal->info->duration_error[1][0][i] / n;
3394 double error1 = st->internal->info->duration_error[1][1][i] / n - a1*a1;
3395 if (error0 > 0.04 && error1 > 0.04) {
3396 st->internal->info->duration_error[0][1][i] = 2e10;
3397 st->internal->info->duration_error[1][1][i] = 2e10;
3398 }
3399 }
3400 }
3401 }
3402
3403 // ignore the first 4 values, they might have some random jitter
3404 if (st->internal->info->duration_count > 3 && is_relative(ts) == is_relative(last))
3405 st->internal->info->duration_gcd = av_gcd(st->internal->info->duration_gcd, duration);
3406 }
3407 if (ts != AV_NOPTS_VALUE)
3408 st->internal->info->last_dts = ts;
3409
3410 return 0;
3411}
3412
3413void ff_rfps_calculate(AVFormatContext *ic)
3414{
3415 int i, j;
3416
3417 for (i = 0; i < ic->nb_streams; i++) {
3418 AVStream *st = ic->streams[i];
3419
3420 if (st->codecpar->codec_type != AVMEDIA_TYPE_VIDEO)
3421 continue;
3422 // the check for tb_unreliable() is not completely correct, since this is not about handling
3423 // an unreliable/inexact time base, but a time base that is finer than necessary, as e.g.
3424 // ipmovie.c produces.
3425 if (tb_unreliable(st->internal->avctx) && st->internal->info->duration_count > 15 && st->internal->info->duration_gcd > FFMAX(1, st->time_base.den/(500LL*st->time_base.num)) && !st->r_frame_rate.num &&
3426 st->internal->info->duration_gcd < INT64_MAX / st->time_base.num)
3427 av_reduce(&st->r_frame_rate.num, &st->r_frame_rate.den, st->time_base.den, st->time_base.num * st->internal->info->duration_gcd, INT_MAX);
3428 if (st->internal->info->duration_count>1 && !st->r_frame_rate.num
3429 && tb_unreliable(st->internal->avctx)) {
3430 int num = 0;
3431 double best_error= 0.01;
3432 AVRational ref_rate = st->r_frame_rate.num ? st->r_frame_rate : av_inv_q(st->time_base);
3433
3434 for (j= 0; j<MAX_STD_TIMEBASES; j++) {
3435 int k;
3436
3437 if (st->internal->info->codec_info_duration &&
3438 st->internal->info->codec_info_duration*av_q2d(st->time_base) < (1001*11.5)/get_std_framerate(j))
3439 continue;
3440 if (!st->internal->info->codec_info_duration && get_std_framerate(j) < 1001*12)
3441 continue;
3442
3443 if (av_q2d(st->time_base) * st->internal->info->rfps_duration_sum / st->internal->info->duration_count < (1001*12.0 * 0.8)/get_std_framerate(j))
3444 continue;
3445
3446 for (k= 0; k<2; k++) {
3447 int n = st->internal->info->duration_count;
3448 double a= st->internal->info->duration_error[k][0][j] / n;
3449 double error= st->internal->info->duration_error[k][1][j]/n - a*a;
3450
3451 if (error < best_error && best_error> 0.000000001) {
3452 best_error= error;
3453 num = get_std_framerate(j);
3454 }
3455 if (error < 0.02)
3456 av_log(ic, AV_LOG_DEBUG, "rfps: %f %f\n", get_std_framerate(j) / 12.0/1001, error);
3457 }
3458 }
3459 // do not increase frame rate by more than 1 % in order to match a standard rate.
3460 if (num && (!ref_rate.num || (double)num/(12*1001) < 1.01 * av_q2d(ref_rate)))
3461 av_reduce(&st->r_frame_rate.num, &st->r_frame_rate.den, num, 12*1001, INT_MAX);
3462 }
3463 if ( !st->avg_frame_rate.num
3464 && st->r_frame_rate.num && st->internal->info->rfps_duration_sum
3465 && st->internal->info->codec_info_duration <= 0
3466 && st->internal->info->duration_count > 2
3467 && fabs(1.0 / (av_q2d(st->r_frame_rate) * av_q2d(st->time_base)) - st->internal->info->rfps_duration_sum / (double)st->internal->info->duration_count) <= 1.0
3468 ) {
3469 av_log(ic, AV_LOG_DEBUG, "Setting avg frame rate based on r frame rate\n");
3470 st->avg_frame_rate = st->r_frame_rate;
3471 }
3472
3473 av_freep(&st->internal->info->duration_error);
3474 st->internal->info->last_dts = AV_NOPTS_VALUE;
3475 st->internal->info->duration_count = 0;
3476 st->internal->info->rfps_duration_sum = 0;
3477 }
3478}
3479
3480static int extract_extradata_check(AVStream *st)
3481{
3482 const AVBitStreamFilter *f;
3483
3484 f = av_bsf_get_by_name("extract_extradata");
3485 if (!f)
3486 return 0;
3487
3488 if (f->codec_ids) {
3489 const enum AVCodecID *ids;
3490 for (ids = f->codec_ids; *ids != AV_CODEC_ID_NONE; ids++)
3491 if (*ids == st->codecpar->codec_id)
3492 return 1;
3493 }
3494
3495 return 0;
3496}
3497
3498static int extract_extradata_init(AVStream *st)
3499{
3500 AVStreamInternal *sti = st->internal;
3501 const AVBitStreamFilter *f;
3502 int ret;
3503
3504 f = av_bsf_get_by_name("extract_extradata");
3505 if (!f)
3506 goto finish;
3507
3508 /* check that the codec id is supported */
3509 ret = extract_extradata_check(st);
3510 if (!ret)
3511 goto finish;
3512
3513 sti->extract_extradata.pkt = av_packet_alloc();
3514 if (!sti->extract_extradata.pkt)
3515 return AVERROR(ENOMEM);
3516
3517 ret = av_bsf_alloc(f, &sti->extract_extradata.bsf);
3518 if (ret < 0)
3519 goto fail;
3520
3521 ret = avcodec_parameters_copy(sti->extract_extradata.bsf->par_in,
3522 st->codecpar);
3523 if (ret < 0)
3524 goto fail;
3525
3526 sti->extract_extradata.bsf->time_base_in = st->time_base;
3527
3528 ret = av_bsf_init(sti->extract_extradata.bsf);
3529 if (ret < 0)
3530 goto fail;
3531
3532finish:
3533 sti->extract_extradata.inited = 1;
3534
3535 return 0;
3536fail:
3537 av_bsf_free(&sti->extract_extradata.bsf);
3538 av_packet_free(&sti->extract_extradata.pkt);
3539 return ret;
3540}
3541
3542static int extract_extradata(AVStream *st, const AVPacket *pkt)
3543{
3544 AVStreamInternal *sti = st->internal;
3545 AVPacket *pkt_ref;
3546 int ret;
3547
3548 if (!sti->extract_extradata.inited) {
3549 ret = extract_extradata_init(st);
3550 if (ret < 0)
3551 return ret;
3552 }
3553
3554 if (sti->extract_extradata.inited && !sti->extract_extradata.bsf)
3555 return 0;
3556
3557 pkt_ref = sti->extract_extradata.pkt;
3558 ret = av_packet_ref(pkt_ref, pkt);
3559 if (ret < 0)
3560 return ret;
3561
3562 ret = av_bsf_send_packet(sti->extract_extradata.bsf, pkt_ref);
3563 if (ret < 0) {
3564 av_packet_unref(pkt_ref);
3565 return ret;
3566 }
3567
3568 while (ret >= 0 && !sti->avctx->extradata) {
3569 ret = av_bsf_receive_packet(sti->extract_extradata.bsf, pkt_ref);
3570 if (ret < 0) {
3571 if (ret != AVERROR(EAGAIN) && ret != AVERROR_EOF)
3572 return ret;
3573 continue;
3574 }
3575
3576 for (int i = 0; i < pkt_ref->side_data_elems; i++) {
3577 AVPacketSideData *side_data = &pkt_ref->side_data[i];
3578 if (side_data->type == AV_PKT_DATA_NEW_EXTRADATA) {
3579 sti->avctx->extradata = side_data->data;
3580 sti->avctx->extradata_size = side_data->size;
3581 side_data->data = NULL;
3582 side_data->size = 0;
3583 break;
3584 }
3585 }
3586 av_packet_unref(pkt_ref);
3587 }
3588
3589 return 0;
3590}
3591
3592static int add_coded_side_data(AVStream *st, AVCodecContext *avctx)
3593{
3594 int i;
3595
3596 for (i = 0; i < avctx->nb_coded_side_data; i++) {
3597 const AVPacketSideData *sd_src = &avctx->coded_side_data[i];
3598 uint8_t *dst_data;
3599 dst_data = av_stream_new_side_data(st, sd_src->type, sd_src->size);
3600 if (!dst_data)
3601 return AVERROR(ENOMEM);
3602 memcpy(dst_data, sd_src->data, sd_src->size);
3603 }
3604 return 0;
3605}
3606
3607int avformat_find_stream_info(AVFormatContext *ic, AVDictionary **options)
3608{
3609 int i, count = 0, ret = 0, j;
3610 int64_t read_size;
3611 AVStream *st;
3612 AVCodecContext *avctx;
3613 AVPacket *pkt1 = ic->internal->pkt;
3614 int64_t old_offset = avio_tell(ic->pb);
3615 // new streams might appear, no options for those
3616 int orig_nb_streams = ic->nb_streams;
3617 int flush_codecs;
3618 int64_t max_analyze_duration = ic->max_analyze_duration;
3619 int64_t max_stream_analyze_duration;
3620 int64_t max_subtitle_analyze_duration;
3621 int64_t probesize = ic->probesize;
3622 int eof_reached = 0;
3623 int *missing_streams = av_opt_ptr(ic->iformat->priv_class, ic->priv_data, "missing_streams");
3624
3625 flush_codecs = probesize > 0;
3626
3627 av_opt_set(ic, "skip_clear", "1", AV_OPT_SEARCH_CHILDREN);
3628
3629 max_stream_analyze_duration = max_analyze_duration;
3630 max_subtitle_analyze_duration = max_analyze_duration;
3631 if (!max_analyze_duration) {
3632 max_stream_analyze_duration =
3633 max_analyze_duration = 5*AV_TIME_BASE;
3634 max_subtitle_analyze_duration = 30*AV_TIME_BASE;
3635 if (!strcmp(ic->iformat->name, "flv"))
3636 max_stream_analyze_duration = 90*AV_TIME_BASE;
3637 if (!strcmp(ic->iformat->name, "mpeg") || !strcmp(ic->iformat->name, "mpegts"))
3638 max_stream_analyze_duration = 7*AV_TIME_BASE;
3639 }
3640
3641 if (ic->pb)
3642 av_log(ic, AV_LOG_DEBUG, "Before avformat_find_stream_info() pos: %"PRId64" bytes read:%"PRId64" seeks:%d nb_streams:%d\n",
3643 avio_tell(ic->pb), ic->pb->bytes_read, ic->pb->seek_count, ic->nb_streams);
3644
3645 for (i = 0; i < ic->nb_streams; i++) {
3646 const AVCodec *codec;
3647 AVDictionary *thread_opt = NULL;
3648 st = ic->streams[i];
3649 avctx = st->internal->avctx;
3650
3651 if (st->codecpar->codec_type == AVMEDIA_TYPE_VIDEO ||
3652 st->codecpar->codec_type == AVMEDIA_TYPE_SUBTITLE) {
3653/* if (!st->time_base.num)
3654 st->time_base = */
3655 if (!avctx->time_base.num)
3656 avctx->time_base = st->time_base;
3657 }
3658
3659 /* check if the caller has overridden the codec id */
3660#if FF_API_LAVF_AVCTX
3661FF_DISABLE_DEPRECATION_WARNINGS
3662 if (st->codec->codec_id != st->internal->orig_codec_id) {
3663 st->codecpar->codec_id = st->codec->codec_id;
3664 st->codecpar->codec_type = st->codec->codec_type;
3665 st->internal->orig_codec_id = st->codec->codec_id;
3666 }
3667FF_ENABLE_DEPRECATION_WARNINGS
3668#endif
3669 // only for the split stuff
3670 if (!st->parser && !(ic->flags & AVFMT_FLAG_NOPARSE) && st->internal->request_probe <= 0) {
3671 st->parser = av_parser_init(st->codecpar->codec_id);
3672 if (st->parser) {
3673 if (st->need_parsing == AVSTREAM_PARSE_HEADERS) {
3674 st->parser->flags |= PARSER_FLAG_COMPLETE_FRAMES;
3675 } else if (st->need_parsing == AVSTREAM_PARSE_FULL_RAW) {
3676 st->parser->flags |= PARSER_FLAG_USE_CODEC_TS;
3677 }
3678 } else if (st->need_parsing) {
3679 av_log(ic, AV_LOG_VERBOSE, "parser not found for codec "
3680 "%s, packets or times may be invalid.\n",
3681 avcodec_get_name(st->codecpar->codec_id));
3682 }
3683 }
3684
3685 if (st->codecpar->codec_id != st->internal->orig_codec_id)
3686 st->internal->orig_codec_id = st->codecpar->codec_id;
3687
3688 ret = avcodec_parameters_to_context(avctx, st->codecpar);
3689 if (ret < 0)
3690 goto find_stream_info_err;
3691 if (st->internal->request_probe <= 0)
3692 st->internal->avctx_inited = 1;
3693
3694 codec = find_probe_decoder(ic, st, st->codecpar->codec_id);
3695
3696 /* Force thread count to 1 since the H.264 decoder will not extract
3697 * SPS and PPS to extradata during multi-threaded decoding. */
3698 av_dict_set(options ? &options[i] : &thread_opt, "threads", "1", 0);
3699 /* Force lowres to 0. The decoder might reduce the video size by the
3700 * lowres factor, and we don't want that propagated to the stream's
3701 * codecpar */
3702 av_dict_set(options ? &options[i] : &thread_opt, "lowres", "0", 0);
3703
3704 if (ic->codec_whitelist)
3705 av_dict_set(options ? &options[i] : &thread_opt, "codec_whitelist", ic->codec_whitelist, 0);
3706
3707 /* Ensure that subtitle_header is properly set. */
3708 if (st->codecpar->codec_type == AVMEDIA_TYPE_SUBTITLE
3709 && codec && !avctx->codec) {
3710 if (avcodec_open2(avctx, codec, options ? &options[i] : &thread_opt) < 0)
3711 av_log(ic, AV_LOG_WARNING,
3712 "Failed to open codec in %s\n",__FUNCTION__);
3713 }
3714
3715 // Try to just open decoders, in case this is enough to get parameters.
3716 if (!has_codec_parameters(st, NULL) && st->internal->request_probe <= 0) {
3717 if (codec && !avctx->codec)
3718 if (avcodec_open2(avctx, codec, options ? &options[i] : &thread_opt) < 0)
3719 av_log(ic, AV_LOG_WARNING,
3720 "Failed to open codec in %s\n",__FUNCTION__);
3721 }
3722 if (!options)
3723 av_dict_free(&thread_opt);
3724 }
3725
3726 for (i = 0; i < ic->nb_streams; i++) {
3727#if FF_API_R_FRAME_RATE
3728 ic->streams[i]->internal->info->last_dts = AV_NOPTS_VALUE;
3729#endif
3730 ic->streams[i]->internal->info->fps_first_dts = AV_NOPTS_VALUE;
3731 ic->streams[i]->internal->info->fps_last_dts = AV_NOPTS_VALUE;
3732 }
3733
3734 read_size = 0;
3735 for (;;) {
3736 const AVPacket *pkt;
3737 int analyzed_all_streams;
3738 if (ff_check_interrupt(&ic->interrupt_callback)) {
3739 ret = AVERROR_EXIT;
3740 av_log(ic, AV_LOG_DEBUG, "interrupted\n");
3741 break;
3742 }
3743
3744 /* check if one codec still needs to be handled */
3745 for (i = 0; i < ic->nb_streams; i++) {
3746 int fps_analyze_framecount = 20;
3747 int count;
3748
3749 st = ic->streams[i];
3750 if (!has_codec_parameters(st, NULL))
3751 break;
3752 /* If the timebase is coarse (like the usual millisecond precision
3753 * of mkv), we need to analyze more frames to reliably arrive at
3754 * the correct fps. */
3755 if (av_q2d(st->time_base) > 0.0005)
3756 fps_analyze_framecount *= 2;
3757 if (!tb_unreliable(st->internal->avctx))
3758 fps_analyze_framecount = 0;
3759 if (ic->fps_probe_size >= 0)
3760 fps_analyze_framecount = ic->fps_probe_size;
3761 if (st->disposition & AV_DISPOSITION_ATTACHED_PIC)
3762 fps_analyze_framecount = 0;
3763 /* variable fps and no guess at the real fps */
3764 count = (ic->iformat->flags & AVFMT_NOTIMESTAMPS) ?
3765 st->internal->info->codec_info_duration_fields/2 :
3766 st->internal->info->duration_count;
3767 if (!(st->r_frame_rate.num && st->avg_frame_rate.num) &&
3768 st->codecpar->codec_type == AVMEDIA_TYPE_VIDEO) {
3769 if (count < fps_analyze_framecount)
3770 break;
3771 }
3772 // Look at the first 3 frames if there is evidence of frame delay
3773 // but the decoder delay is not set.
3774 if (st->internal->info->frame_delay_evidence && count < 2 && st->internal->avctx->has_b_frames == 0)
3775 break;
3776 if (!st->internal->avctx->extradata &&
3777 (!st->internal->extract_extradata.inited ||
3778 st->internal->extract_extradata.bsf) &&
3779 extract_extradata_check(st))
3780 break;
3781 if (st->first_dts == AV_NOPTS_VALUE &&
3782 !(ic->iformat->flags & AVFMT_NOTIMESTAMPS) &&
3783 st->codec_info_nb_frames < ((st->disposition & AV_DISPOSITION_ATTACHED_PIC) ? 1 : ic->max_ts_probe) &&
3784 (st->codecpar->codec_type == AVMEDIA_TYPE_VIDEO ||
3785 st->codecpar->codec_type == AVMEDIA_TYPE_AUDIO))
3786 break;
3787 }
3788 analyzed_all_streams = 0;
3789 if (!missing_streams || !*missing_streams)
3790 if (i == ic->nb_streams) {
3791 analyzed_all_streams = 1;
3792 /* NOTE: If the format has no header, then we need to read some
3793 * packets to get most of the streams, so we cannot stop here. */
3794 if (!(ic->ctx_flags & AVFMTCTX_NOHEADER)) {
3795 /* If we found the info for all the codecs, we can stop. */
3796 ret = count;
3797 av_log(ic, AV_LOG_DEBUG, "All info found\n");
3798 flush_codecs = 0;
3799 break;
3800 }
3801 }
3802 /* We did not get all the codec info, but we read too much data. */
3803 if (read_size >= probesize) {
3804 ret = count;
3805 av_log(ic, AV_LOG_DEBUG,
3806 "Probe buffer size limit of %"PRId64" bytes reached\n", probesize);
3807 for (i = 0; i < ic->nb_streams; i++)
3808 if (!ic->streams[i]->r_frame_rate.num &&
3809 ic->streams[i]->internal->info->duration_count <= 1 &&
3810 ic->streams[i]->codecpar->codec_type == AVMEDIA_TYPE_VIDEO &&
3811 strcmp(ic->iformat->name, "image2"))
3812 av_log(ic, AV_LOG_WARNING,
3813 "Stream #%d: not enough frames to estimate rate; "
3814 "consider increasing probesize\n", i);
3815 break;
3816 }
3817
3818 /* NOTE: A new stream can be added there if no header in file
3819 * (AVFMTCTX_NOHEADER). */
3820 ret = read_frame_internal(ic, pkt1);
3821 if (ret == AVERROR(EAGAIN))
3822 continue;
3823
3824 if (ret < 0) {
3825 /* EOF or error*/
3826 eof_reached = 1;
3827 break;
3828 }
3829
3830 if (!(ic->flags & AVFMT_FLAG_NOBUFFER)) {
3831 ret = avpriv_packet_list_put(&ic->internal->packet_buffer,
3832 &ic->internal->packet_buffer_end,
3833 pkt1, NULL, 0);
3834 if (ret < 0)
3835 goto unref_then_goto_end;
3836
3837 pkt = &ic->internal->packet_buffer_end->pkt;
3838 } else {
3839 pkt = pkt1;
3840 }
3841
3842 st = ic->streams[pkt->stream_index];
3843 if (!(st->disposition & AV_DISPOSITION_ATTACHED_PIC))
3844 read_size += pkt->size;
3845
3846 avctx = st->internal->avctx;
3847 if (!st->internal->avctx_inited) {
3848 ret = avcodec_parameters_to_context(avctx, st->codecpar);
3849 if (ret < 0)
3850 goto unref_then_goto_end;
3851 st->internal->avctx_inited = 1;
3852 }
3853
3854 if (pkt->dts != AV_NOPTS_VALUE && st->codec_info_nb_frames > 1) {
3855 /* check for non-increasing dts */
3856 if (st->internal->info->fps_last_dts != AV_NOPTS_VALUE &&
3857 st->internal->info->fps_last_dts >= pkt->dts) {
3858 av_log(ic, AV_LOG_DEBUG,
3859 "Non-increasing DTS in stream %d: packet %d with DTS "
3860 "%"PRId64", packet %d with DTS %"PRId64"\n",
3861 st->index, st->internal->info->fps_last_dts_idx,
3862 st->internal->info->fps_last_dts, st->codec_info_nb_frames,
3863 pkt->dts);
3864 st->internal->info->fps_first_dts =
3865 st->internal->info->fps_last_dts = AV_NOPTS_VALUE;
3866 }
3867 /* Check for a discontinuity in dts. If the difference in dts
3868 * is more than 1000 times the average packet duration in the
3869 * sequence, we treat it as a discontinuity. */
3870 if (st->internal->info->fps_last_dts != AV_NOPTS_VALUE &&
3871 st->internal->info->fps_last_dts_idx > st->internal->info->fps_first_dts_idx &&
3872 (pkt->dts - (uint64_t)st->internal->info->fps_last_dts) / 1000 >
3873 (st->internal->info->fps_last_dts - (uint64_t)st->internal->info->fps_first_dts) /
3874 (st->internal->info->fps_last_dts_idx - st->internal->info->fps_first_dts_idx)) {
3875 av_log(ic, AV_LOG_WARNING,
3876 "DTS discontinuity in stream %d: packet %d with DTS "
3877 "%"PRId64", packet %d with DTS %"PRId64"\n",
3878 st->index, st->internal->info->fps_last_dts_idx,
3879 st->internal->info->fps_last_dts, st->codec_info_nb_frames,
3880 pkt->dts);
3881 st->internal->info->fps_first_dts =
3882 st->internal->info->fps_last_dts = AV_NOPTS_VALUE;
3883 }
3884
3885 /* update stored dts values */
3886 if (st->internal->info->fps_first_dts == AV_NOPTS_VALUE) {
3887 st->internal->info->fps_first_dts = pkt->dts;
3888 st->internal->info->fps_first_dts_idx = st->codec_info_nb_frames;
3889 }
3890 st->internal->info->fps_last_dts = pkt->dts;
3891 st->internal->info->fps_last_dts_idx = st->codec_info_nb_frames;
3892 }
3893 if (st->codec_info_nb_frames>1) {
3894 int64_t t = 0;
3895 int64_t limit;
3896
3897 if (st->time_base.den > 0)
3898 t = av_rescale_q(st->internal->info->codec_info_duration, st->time_base, AV_TIME_BASE_Q);
3899 if (st->avg_frame_rate.num > 0)
3900 t = FFMAX(t, av_rescale_q(st->codec_info_nb_frames, av_inv_q(st->avg_frame_rate), AV_TIME_BASE_Q));
3901
3902 if ( t == 0
3903 && st->codec_info_nb_frames>30
3904 && st->internal->info->fps_first_dts != AV_NOPTS_VALUE
3905 && st->internal->info->fps_last_dts != AV_NOPTS_VALUE) {
3906 int64_t dur = av_sat_sub64(st->internal->info->fps_last_dts, st->internal->info->fps_first_dts);
3907 t = FFMAX(t, av_rescale_q(dur, st->time_base, AV_TIME_BASE_Q));
3908 }
3909
3910 if (analyzed_all_streams) limit = max_analyze_duration;
3911 else if (avctx->codec_type == AVMEDIA_TYPE_SUBTITLE) limit = max_subtitle_analyze_duration;
3912 else limit = max_stream_analyze_duration;
3913
3914 if (t >= limit) {
3915 av_log(ic, AV_LOG_VERBOSE, "max_analyze_duration %"PRId64" reached at %"PRId64" microseconds st:%d\n",
3916 limit,
3917 t, pkt->stream_index);
3918 if (ic->flags & AVFMT_FLAG_NOBUFFER)
3919 av_packet_unref(pkt1);
3920 break;
3921 }
3922 if (pkt->duration) {
3923 if (avctx->codec_type == AVMEDIA_TYPE_SUBTITLE && pkt->pts != AV_NOPTS_VALUE && st->start_time != AV_NOPTS_VALUE && pkt->pts >= st->start_time) {
3924 st->internal->info->codec_info_duration = FFMIN(pkt->pts - st->start_time, st->internal->info->codec_info_duration + pkt->duration);
3925 } else
3926 st->internal->info->codec_info_duration += pkt->duration;
3927 st->internal->info->codec_info_duration_fields += st->parser && st->need_parsing && avctx->ticks_per_frame ==2 ? st->parser->repeat_pict + 1 : 2;
3928 }
3929 }
3930 if (st->codecpar->codec_type == AVMEDIA_TYPE_VIDEO) {
3931#if FF_API_R_FRAME_RATE
3932 ff_rfps_add_frame(ic, st, pkt->dts);
3933#endif
3934 if (pkt->dts != pkt->pts && pkt->dts != AV_NOPTS_VALUE && pkt->pts != AV_NOPTS_VALUE)
3935 st->internal->info->frame_delay_evidence = 1;
3936 }
3937 if (!st->internal->avctx->extradata) {
3938 ret = extract_extradata(st, pkt);
3939 if (ret < 0)
3940 goto unref_then_goto_end;
3941 }
3942
3943 /* If still no information, we try to open the codec and to
3944 * decompress the frame. We try to avoid that in most cases as
3945 * it takes longer and uses more memory. For MPEG-4, we need to
3946 * decompress for QuickTime.
3947 *
3948 * If AV_CODEC_CAP_CHANNEL_CONF is set this will force decoding of at
3949 * least one frame of codec data, this makes sure the codec initializes
3950 * the channel configuration and does not only trust the values from
3951 * the container. */
3952 try_decode_frame(ic, st, pkt,
3953 (options && i < orig_nb_streams) ? &options[i] : NULL);
3954
3955 if (ic->flags & AVFMT_FLAG_NOBUFFER)
3956 av_packet_unref(pkt1);
3957
3958 st->codec_info_nb_frames++;
3959 count++;
3960 }
3961
3962 if (eof_reached) {
3963 int stream_index;
3964 for (stream_index = 0; stream_index < ic->nb_streams; stream_index++) {
3965 st = ic->streams[stream_index];
3966 avctx = st->internal->avctx;
3967 if (!has_codec_parameters(st, NULL)) {
3968 const AVCodec *codec = find_probe_decoder(ic, st, st->codecpar->codec_id);
3969 if (codec && !avctx->codec) {
3970 AVDictionary *opts = NULL;
3971 if (ic->codec_whitelist)
3972 av_dict_set(&opts, "codec_whitelist", ic->codec_whitelist, 0);
3973 if (avcodec_open2(avctx, codec, (options && stream_index < orig_nb_streams) ? &options[stream_index] : &opts) < 0)
3974 av_log(ic, AV_LOG_WARNING,
3975 "Failed to open codec in %s\n",__FUNCTION__);
3976 av_dict_free(&opts);
3977 }
3978 }
3979
3980 // EOF already reached while reading the stream above.
3981 // So continue with reoordering DTS with whatever delay we have.
3982 if (ic->internal->packet_buffer && !has_decode_delay_been_guessed(st)) {
3983 update_dts_from_pts(ic, stream_index, ic->internal->packet_buffer);
3984 }
3985 }
3986 }
3987
3988 if (flush_codecs) {
3989 AVPacket *empty_pkt = ic->internal->pkt;
3990 int err = 0;
3991 av_packet_unref(empty_pkt);
3992
3993 for (i = 0; i < ic->nb_streams; i++) {
3994
3995 st = ic->streams[i];
3996
3997 /* flush the decoders */
3998 if (st->internal->info->found_decoder == 1) {
3999 do {
4000 err = try_decode_frame(ic, st, empty_pkt,
4001 (options && i < orig_nb_streams)
4002 ? &options[i] : NULL);
4003 } while (err > 0 && !has_codec_parameters(st, NULL));
4004
4005 if (err < 0) {
4006 av_log(ic, AV_LOG_INFO,
4007 "decoding for stream %d failed\n", st->index);
4008 }
4009 }
4010 }
4011 }
4012
4013 ff_rfps_calculate(ic);
4014
4015 for (i = 0; i < ic->nb_streams; i++) {
4016 st = ic->streams[i];
4017 avctx = st->internal->avctx;
4018 if (avctx->codec_type == AVMEDIA_TYPE_VIDEO) {
4019 if (avctx->codec_id == AV_CODEC_ID_RAWVIDEO && !avctx->codec_tag && !avctx->bits_per_coded_sample) {
4020 uint32_t tag= avcodec_pix_fmt_to_codec_tag(avctx->pix_fmt);
4021 if (avpriv_find_pix_fmt(avpriv_get_raw_pix_fmt_tags(), tag) == avctx->pix_fmt)
4022 avctx->codec_tag= tag;
4023 }
4024
4025 /* estimate average framerate if not set by demuxer */
4026 if (st->internal->info->codec_info_duration_fields &&
4027 !st->avg_frame_rate.num &&
4028 st->internal->info->codec_info_duration) {
4029 int best_fps = 0;
4030 double best_error = 0.01;
4031 AVRational codec_frame_rate = avctx->framerate;
4032
4033 if (st->internal->info->codec_info_duration >= INT64_MAX / st->time_base.num / 2||
4034 st->internal->info->codec_info_duration_fields >= INT64_MAX / st->time_base.den ||
4035 st->internal->info->codec_info_duration < 0)
4036 continue;
4037 av_reduce(&st->avg_frame_rate.num, &st->avg_frame_rate.den,
4038 st->internal->info->codec_info_duration_fields * (int64_t) st->time_base.den,
4039 st->internal->info->codec_info_duration * 2 * (int64_t) st->time_base.num, 60000);
4040
4041 /* Round guessed framerate to a "standard" framerate if it's
4042 * within 1% of the original estimate. */
4043 for (j = 0; j < MAX_STD_TIMEBASES; j++) {
4044 AVRational std_fps = { get_std_framerate(j), 12 * 1001 };
4045 double error = fabs(av_q2d(st->avg_frame_rate) /
4046 av_q2d(std_fps) - 1);
4047
4048 if (error < best_error) {
4049 best_error = error;
4050 best_fps = std_fps.num;
4051 }
4052
4053 if (ic->internal->prefer_codec_framerate && codec_frame_rate.num > 0 && codec_frame_rate.den > 0) {
4054 error = fabs(av_q2d(codec_frame_rate) /
4055 av_q2d(std_fps) - 1);
4056 if (error < best_error) {
4057 best_error = error;
4058 best_fps = std_fps.num;
4059 }
4060 }
4061 }
4062 if (best_fps)
4063 av_reduce(&st->avg_frame_rate.num, &st->avg_frame_rate.den,
4064 best_fps, 12 * 1001, INT_MAX);
4065 }
4066
4067 if (!st->r_frame_rate.num) {
4068 if ( avctx->time_base.den * (int64_t) st->time_base.num
4069 <= avctx->time_base.num * avctx->ticks_per_frame * (uint64_t) st->time_base.den) {
4070 av_reduce(&st->r_frame_rate.num, &st->r_frame_rate.den,
4071 avctx->time_base.den, (int64_t)avctx->time_base.num * avctx->ticks_per_frame, INT_MAX);
4072 } else {
4073 st->r_frame_rate.num = st->time_base.den;
4074 st->r_frame_rate.den = st->time_base.num;
4075 }
4076 }
4077 if (st->internal->display_aspect_ratio.num && st->internal->display_aspect_ratio.den) {
4078 AVRational hw_ratio = { avctx->height, avctx->width };
4079 st->sample_aspect_ratio = av_mul_q(st->internal->display_aspect_ratio,
4080 hw_ratio);
4081 }
4082 } else if (avctx->codec_type == AVMEDIA_TYPE_AUDIO) {
4083 if (!avctx->bits_per_coded_sample)
4084 avctx->bits_per_coded_sample =
4085 av_get_bits_per_sample(avctx->codec_id);
4086 // set stream disposition based on audio service type
4087 switch (avctx->audio_service_type) {
4088 case AV_AUDIO_SERVICE_TYPE_EFFECTS:
4089 st->disposition = AV_DISPOSITION_CLEAN_EFFECTS;
4090 break;
4091 case AV_AUDIO_SERVICE_TYPE_VISUALLY_IMPAIRED:
4092 st->disposition = AV_DISPOSITION_VISUAL_IMPAIRED;
4093 break;
4094 case AV_AUDIO_SERVICE_TYPE_HEARING_IMPAIRED:
4095 st->disposition = AV_DISPOSITION_HEARING_IMPAIRED;
4096 break;
4097 case AV_AUDIO_SERVICE_TYPE_COMMENTARY:
4098 st->disposition = AV_DISPOSITION_COMMENT;
4099 break;
4100 case AV_AUDIO_SERVICE_TYPE_KARAOKE:
4101 st->disposition = AV_DISPOSITION_KARAOKE;
4102 break;
4103 }
4104 }
4105 }
4106
4107 if (probesize)
4108 estimate_timings(ic, old_offset);
4109
4110 av_opt_set(ic, "skip_clear", "0", AV_OPT_SEARCH_CHILDREN);
4111
4112 if (ret >= 0 && ic->nb_streams)
4113 /* We could not have all the codec parameters before EOF. */
4114 ret = -1;
4115 for (i = 0; i < ic->nb_streams; i++) {
4116 const char *errmsg;
4117 st = ic->streams[i];
4118
4119 /* if no packet was ever seen, update context now for has_codec_parameters */
4120 if (!st->internal->avctx_inited) {
4121 if (st->codecpar->codec_type == AVMEDIA_TYPE_AUDIO &&
4122 st->codecpar->format == AV_SAMPLE_FMT_NONE)
4123 st->codecpar->format = st->internal->avctx->sample_fmt;
4124 ret = avcodec_parameters_to_context(st->internal->avctx, st->codecpar);
4125 if (ret < 0)
4126 goto find_stream_info_err;
4127 }
4128 if (!has_codec_parameters(st, &errmsg)) {
4129 char buf[256];
4130 avcodec_string(buf, sizeof(buf), st->internal->avctx, 0);
4131 av_log(ic, AV_LOG_WARNING,
4132 "Could not find codec parameters for stream %d (%s): %s\n"
4133 "Consider increasing the value for the 'analyzeduration' (%"PRId64") and 'probesize' (%"PRId64") options\n",
4134 i, buf, errmsg, ic->max_analyze_duration, ic->probesize);
4135 } else {
4136 ret = 0;
4137 }
4138 }
4139
4140 ret = compute_chapters_end(ic);
4141 if (ret < 0)
4142 goto find_stream_info_err;
4143
4144 /* update the stream parameters from the internal codec contexts */
4145 for (i = 0; i < ic->nb_streams; i++) {
4146 st = ic->streams[i];
4147
4148 if (st->internal->avctx_inited) {
4149 ret = avcodec_parameters_from_context(st->codecpar, st->internal->avctx);
4150 if (ret < 0)
4151 goto find_stream_info_err;
4152 ret = add_coded_side_data(st, st->internal->avctx);
4153 if (ret < 0)
4154 goto find_stream_info_err;
4155 }
4156
4157#if FF_API_LAVF_AVCTX
4158FF_DISABLE_DEPRECATION_WARNINGS
4159 ret = avcodec_parameters_to_context(st->codec, st->codecpar);
4160 if (ret < 0)
4161 goto find_stream_info_err;
4162
4163 // The old API (AVStream.codec) "requires" the resolution to be adjusted
4164 // by the lowres factor.
4165 if (st->internal->avctx->lowres && st->internal->avctx->width) {
4166 st->codec->lowres = st->internal->avctx->lowres;
4167 st->codec->width = st->internal->avctx->width;
4168 st->codec->height = st->internal->avctx->height;
4169 }
4170
4171 if (st->codec->codec_tag != MKTAG('t','m','c','d')) {
4172 st->codec->time_base = st->internal->avctx->time_base;
4173 st->codec->ticks_per_frame = st->internal->avctx->ticks_per_frame;
4174 }
4175 st->codec->framerate = st->avg_frame_rate;
4176
4177 if (st->internal->avctx->subtitle_header) {
4178 st->codec->subtitle_header = av_malloc(st->internal->avctx->subtitle_header_size);
4179 if (!st->codec->subtitle_header)
4180 goto find_stream_info_err;
4181 st->codec->subtitle_header_size = st->internal->avctx->subtitle_header_size;
4182 memcpy(st->codec->subtitle_header, st->internal->avctx->subtitle_header,
4183 st->codec->subtitle_header_size);
4184 }
4185
4186 // Fields unavailable in AVCodecParameters
4187 st->codec->coded_width = st->internal->avctx->coded_width;
4188 st->codec->coded_height = st->internal->avctx->coded_height;
4189 st->codec->properties = st->internal->avctx->properties;
4190FF_ENABLE_DEPRECATION_WARNINGS
4191#endif
4192
4193 st->internal->avctx_inited = 0;
4194 }
4195
4196find_stream_info_err:
4197 for (i = 0; i < ic->nb_streams; i++) {
4198 st = ic->streams[i];
4199 if (st->internal->info)
4200 av_freep(&st->internal->info->duration_error);
4201 avcodec_close(ic->streams[i]->internal->avctx);
4202 av_freep(&ic->streams[i]->internal->info);
4203 av_bsf_free(&ic->streams[i]->internal->extract_extradata.bsf);
4204 av_packet_free(&ic->streams[i]->internal->extract_extradata.pkt);
4205 }
4206 if (ic->pb)
4207 av_log(ic, AV_LOG_DEBUG, "After avformat_find_stream_info() pos: %"PRId64" bytes read:%"PRId64" seeks:%d frames:%d\n",
4208 avio_tell(ic->pb), ic->pb->bytes_read, ic->pb->seek_count, count);
4209 return ret;
4210
4211unref_then_goto_end:
4212 av_packet_unref(pkt1);
4213 goto find_stream_info_err;
4214}

4232
4233int av_find_best_stream(AVFormatContext *ic, enum AVMediaType type,
4234 int wanted_stream_nb, int related_stream,
4235 AVCodec **decoder_ret, int flags)
4236{
4237 int i, nb_streams = ic->nb_streams;
4238 int ret = AVERROR_STREAM_NOT_FOUND;
4239 int best_count = -1, best_multiframe = -1, best_disposition = -1;
4240 int count, multiframe, disposition;
4241 int64_t best_bitrate = -1;
4242 int64_t bitrate;
4243 unsigned *program = NULL;
4244 const AVCodec *decoder = NULL, *best_decoder = NULL;
4245
4246 if (related_stream >= 0 && wanted_stream_nb < 0) {
4247 AVProgram *p = av_find_program_from_stream(ic, NULL, related_stream);
4248 if (p) {
4249 program = p->stream_index;
4250 nb_streams = p->nb_stream_indexes;
4251 }
4252 }
4253 for (i = 0; i < nb_streams; i++) {
4254 int real_stream_index = program ? program[i] : i;
4255 AVStream *st = ic->streams[real_stream_index];
4256 AVCodecParameters *par = st->codecpar;
4257 if (par->codec_type != type)
4258 continue;
4259 if (wanted_stream_nb >= 0 && real_stream_index != wanted_stream_nb)
4260 continue;
4261 if (type == AVMEDIA_TYPE_AUDIO && !(par->channels && par->sample_rate))
4262 continue;
4263 if (decoder_ret) {
4264 decoder = find_decoder(ic, st, par->codec_id);
4265 if (!decoder) {
4266 if (ret < 0)
4267 ret = AVERROR_DECODER_NOT_FOUND;
4268 continue;
4269 }
4270 }
4271 disposition = !(st->disposition & (AV_DISPOSITION_HEARING_IMPAIRED | AV_DISPOSITION_VISUAL_IMPAIRED))
4272 + !! (st->disposition & AV_DISPOSITION_DEFAULT);
4273 count = st->codec_info_nb_frames;
4274 bitrate = par->bit_rate;
4275 multiframe = FFMIN(5, count);
4276 if ((best_disposition > disposition) ||
4277 (best_disposition == disposition && best_multiframe > multiframe) ||
4278 (best_disposition == disposition && best_multiframe == multiframe && best_bitrate > bitrate) ||
4279 (best_disposition == disposition && best_multiframe == multiframe && best_bitrate == bitrate && best_count >= count))
4280 continue;
4281 best_disposition = disposition;
4282 best_count = count;
4283 best_bitrate = bitrate;
4284 best_multiframe = multiframe;
4285 ret = real_stream_index;
4286 best_decoder = decoder;
4287 if (program && i == nb_streams - 1 && ret < 0) {
4288 program = NULL;
4289 nb_streams = ic->nb_streams;
4290 /* no related stream found, try again with everything */
4291 i = 0;
4292 }
4293 }
4294 if (decoder_ret)
4295 *decoder_ret = (AVCodec*)best_decoder;
4296 return ret;
4297}

4319int ff_stream_encode_params_copy(AVStream *dst, const AVStream *src)
4320{
4321 int ret, i;
4322
4323 dst->id = src->id;
4324 dst->time_base = src->time_base;
4325 dst->nb_frames = src->nb_frames;
4326 dst->disposition = src->disposition;
4327 dst->sample_aspect_ratio = src->sample_aspect_ratio;
4328 dst->avg_frame_rate = src->avg_frame_rate;
4329 dst->r_frame_rate = src->r_frame_rate;
4330
4331 av_dict_free(&dst->metadata);
4332 ret = av_dict_copy(&dst->metadata, src->metadata, 0);
4333 if (ret < 0)
4334 return ret;
4335
4336 ret = avcodec_parameters_copy(dst->codecpar, src->codecpar);
4337 if (ret < 0)
4338 return ret;
4339
4340 /* Free existing side data*/
4341 for (i = 0; i < dst->nb_side_data; i++)
4342 av_free(dst->side_data[i].data);
4343 av_freep(&dst->side_data);
4344 dst->nb_side_data = 0;
4345
4346 /* Copy side data if present */
4347 if (src->nb_side_data) {
4348 dst->side_data = av_mallocz_array(src->nb_side_data,
4349 sizeof(AVPacketSideData));
4350 if (!dst->side_data)
4351 return AVERROR(ENOMEM);
4352 dst->nb_side_data = src->nb_side_data;
4353
4354 for (i = 0; i < src->nb_side_data; i++) {
4355 uint8_t *data = av_memdup(src->side_data[i].data,
4356 src->side_data[i].size);
4357 if (!data)
4358 return AVERROR(ENOMEM);
4359 dst->side_data[i].type = src->side_data[i].type;
4360 dst->side_data[i].size = src->side_data[i].size;
4361 dst->side_data[i].data = data;
4362 }
4363 }
4364
4365#if FF_API_LAVF_FFSERVER
4366FF_DISABLE_DEPRECATION_WARNINGS
4367 av_freep(&dst->recommended_encoder_configuration);
4368 if (src->recommended_encoder_configuration) {
4369 const char *conf_str = src->recommended_encoder_configuration;
4370 dst->recommended_encoder_configuration = av_strdup(conf_str);
4371 if (!dst->recommended_encoder_configuration)
4372 return AVERROR(ENOMEM);
4373 }
4374FF_ENABLE_DEPRECATION_WARNINGS
4375#endif
4376
4377 return 0;
4378}

4440{

4442

4444 return;

4446 if (s->oformat && s->oformat->deinit && s->internal->initialized)
4447 s->oformat->deinit(s);
4448
4449 av_opt_free(s);

4451 av_opt_free(s->priv_data);

4455 for (i = 0; i < s->nb_streams; i++)

4460 av_dict_free(&s->programs[i]->metadata);

4512AVStream *avformat_new_stream(AVFormatContext *s, const AVCodec *c)
4513{
4514 AVStream *st;
4515 int i;
4516 AVStream **streams;
4517
4518 if (s->nb_streams >= FFMIN(s->max_streams, INT_MAX/sizeof(*streams))) {
4519 if (s->max_streams < INT_MAX/sizeof(*streams))
4520 av_log(s, AV_LOG_ERROR, "Number of streams exceeds max_streams parameter (%d), see the documentation if you wish to increase it\n", s->max_streams);
4521 return NULL;
4522 }
4523 streams = av_realloc_array(s->streams, s->nb_streams + 1, sizeof(*streams));
4524 if (!streams)
4525 return NULL;
4526 s->streams = streams;
4527
4528 st = av_mallocz(sizeof(AVStream));
4529 if (!st)
4530 return NULL;
4531
4532#if FF_API_LAVF_AVCTX
4533FF_DISABLE_DEPRECATION_WARNINGS
4534 st->codec = avcodec_alloc_context3(c);
4535 if (!st->codec) {
4536 av_free(st);
4537 return NULL;
4538 }
4539FF_ENABLE_DEPRECATION_WARNINGS
4540#endif
4541
4542 st->internal = av_mallocz(sizeof(*st->internal));
4543 if (!st->internal)
4544 goto fail;
4545
4546 st->internal->info = av_mallocz(sizeof(*st->internal->info));
4547 if (!st->internal->info)
4548 goto fail;
4549 st->internal->info->last_dts = AV_NOPTS_VALUE;
4550
4551 st->codecpar = avcodec_parameters_alloc();
4552 if (!st->codecpar)
4553 goto fail;
4554
4555 st->internal->avctx = avcodec_alloc_context3(NULL);
4556 if (!st->internal->avctx)
4557 goto fail;
4558
4559 if (s->iformat) {
4560#if FF_API_LAVF_AVCTX
4561FF_DISABLE_DEPRECATION_WARNINGS
4562 /* no default bitrate if decoding */
4563 st->codec->bit_rate = 0;
4564FF_ENABLE_DEPRECATION_WARNINGS
4565#endif
4566
4567 /* default pts setting is MPEG-like */
4568 avpriv_set_pts_info(st, 33, 1, 90000);
4569 /* we set the current DTS to 0 so that formats without any timestamps
4570 * but durations get some timestamps, formats with some unknown
4571 * timestamps have their first few packets buffered and the
4572 * timestamps corrected before they are returned to the user */
4573 st->cur_dts = RELATIVE_TS_BASE;
4574 } else {
4575 st->cur_dts = AV_NOPTS_VALUE;
4576 }
4577
4578 st->index = s->nb_streams;
4579 st->start_time = AV_NOPTS_VALUE;
4580 st->duration = AV_NOPTS_VALUE;

4716
4717uint64_t ff_get_formatted_ntp_time(uint64_t ntp_time_us)
4718{
4719 uint64_t ntp_ts, frac_part, sec;
4720 uint32_t usec;
4721
4722 //current ntp time in seconds and micro seconds
4723 sec = ntp_time_us / 1000000;
4724 usec = ntp_time_us % 1000000;
4725
4726 //encoding in ntp timestamp format
4727 frac_part = usec * 0xFFFFFFFFULL;
4728 frac_part /= 1000000;
4729
4730 if (sec > 0xFFFFFFFFULL)
4731 av_log(NULL, AV_LOG_WARNING, "NTP time format roll over detected\n");
4732
4733 ntp_ts = sec << 32;
4734 ntp_ts |= frac_part;
4735
4736 return ntp_ts;
4737}

4739int av_get_frame_filename2(char *buf, int buf_size, const char *path, int number, int flags)
4740{
4741 const char *p;
4742 char *q, buf1[20], c;
4743 int nd, len, percentd_found;
4744
4745 q = buf;
4746 p = path;
4747 percentd_found = 0;
4748 for (;;) {
4749 c = *p++;
4750 if (c == '\0')
4751 break;
4752 if (c == '%') {
4753 do {
4754 nd = 0;
4755 while (av_isdigit(*p)) {
4756 if (nd >= INT_MAX / 10 - 255)
4757 goto fail;
4758 nd = nd * 10 + *p++ - '0';
4759 }
4760 c = *p++;
4761 } while (av_isdigit(c));
4762
4763 switch (c) {
4764 case '%':
4765 goto addchar;
4766 case 'd':
4767 if (!(flags & AV_FRAME_FILENAME_FLAGS_MULTIPLE) && percentd_found)
4768 goto fail;
4769 percentd_found = 1;
4770 if (number < 0)
4771 nd += 1;
4772 snprintf(buf1, sizeof(buf1), "%0*d", nd, number);
4773 len = strlen(buf1);
4774 if ((q - buf + len) > buf_size - 1)
4775 goto fail;
4776 memcpy(q, buf1, len);
4777 q += len;
4778 break;
4779 default:
4780 goto fail;
4781 }
4782 } else {
4783addchar:
4784 if ((q - buf) < buf_size - 1)
4785 *q++ = c;
4786 }
4787 }
4788 if (!percentd_found)
4789 goto fail;
4790 *q = '\0';
4791 return 0;
4792fail:
4793 *q = '\0';
4794 return -1;
4795}

4797int av_get_frame_filename(char *buf, int buf_size, const char *path, int number)
4798{
4799 return av_get_frame_filename2(buf, buf_size, path, number, 0);
4800}
4801
4802void av_url_split(char *proto, int proto_size,
4803 char *authorization, int authorization_size,
4804 char *hostname, int hostname_size,
4805 int *port_ptr, char *path, int path_size, const char *url)
4806{
4807 const char *p, *ls, *at, *at2, *col, *brk;
4808
4809 if (port_ptr)
4810 *port_ptr = -1;
4811 if (proto_size > 0)
4812 proto[0] = 0;
4813 if (authorization_size > 0)
4814 authorization[0] = 0;
4815 if (hostname_size > 0)
4816 hostname[0] = 0;
4817 if (path_size > 0)
4818 path[0] = 0;
4819
4820 /* parse protocol */
4821 if ((p = strchr(url, ':'))) {
4822 av_strlcpy(proto, url, FFMIN(proto_size, p + 1 - url));
4823 p++; /* skip ':' */
4824 if (*p == '/')
4825 p++;
4826 if (*p == '/')
4827 p++;
4828 } else {
4829 /* no protocol means plain filename */
4830 av_strlcpy(path, url, path_size);
4831 return;
4832 }
4833
4834 /* separate path from hostname */
4835 ls = p + strcspn(p, "/?#");
4836 av_strlcpy(path, ls, path_size);
4837
4838 /* the rest is hostname, use that to parse auth/port */
4839 if (ls != p) {
4840 /* authorization (user[:pass]@hostname) */
4841 at2 = p;
4842 while ((at = strchr(p, '@')) && at < ls) {
4843 av_strlcpy(authorization, at2,
4844 FFMIN(authorization_size, at + 1 - at2));
4845 p = at + 1; /* skip '@' */
4846 }
4847
4848 if (*p == '[' && (brk = strchr(p, ']')) && brk < ls) {
4849 /* [host]:port */
4850 av_strlcpy(hostname, p + 1,
4851 FFMIN(hostname_size, brk - p));
4852 if (brk[1] == ':' && port_ptr)
4853 *port_ptr = atoi(brk + 2);
4854 } else if ((col = strchr(p, ':')) && col < ls) {
4855 av_strlcpy(hostname, p,
4856 FFMIN(col + 1 - p, hostname_size));
4857 if (port_ptr)
4858 *port_ptr = atoi(col + 1);
4859 } else
4860 av_strlcpy(hostname, p,
4861 FFMIN(ls + 1 - p, hostname_size));
4862 }
4863}

4865int ff_mkdir_p(const char *path)
4866{
4867 int ret = 0;
4868 char *temp = av_strdup(path);
4869 char *pos = temp;
4870 char tmp_ch = '\0';
4871
4872 if (!path || !temp) {
4873 return -1;
4874 }
4875
4876 if (!av_strncasecmp(temp, "/", 1) || !av_strncasecmp(temp, "\\", 1)) {
4877 pos++;
4878 } else if (!av_strncasecmp(temp, "./", 2) || !av_strncasecmp(temp, ".\\", 2)) {
4879 pos += 2;
4880 }
4881
4882 for ( ; *pos != '\0'; ++pos) {
4883 if (*pos == '/' || *pos == '\\') {
4884 tmp_ch = *pos;
4885 *pos = '\0';
4886 ret = mkdir(temp, 0755);
4887 *pos = tmp_ch;
4888 }
4889 }
4890
4891 if ((*(pos - 1) != '/') || (*(pos - 1) != '\\')) {
4892 ret = mkdir(temp, 0755);
4893 }
4894
4895 av_free(temp);
4896 return ret;
4897}

4899char *ff_data_to_hex(char *buff, const uint8_t *src, int s, int lowercase)
4900{
4901 int i;
4902 static const char hex_table_uc[16] = { '0', '1', '2', '3',
4903 '4', '5', '6', '7',
4904 '8', '9', 'A', 'B',
4905 'C', 'D', 'E', 'F' };
4906 static const char hex_table_lc[16] = { '0', '1', '2', '3',
4907 '4', '5', '6', '7',
4908 '8', '9', 'a', 'b',
4909 'c', 'd', 'e', 'f' };
4910 const char *hex_table = lowercase ? hex_table_lc : hex_table_uc;
4911
4912 for (i = 0; i < s; i++) {
4913 buff[i * 2] = hex_table[src[i] >> 4];
4914 buff[i * 2 + 1] = hex_table[src[i] & 0xF];
4915 }
4916
4917 return buff;
4918}
4919
4920int ff_hex_to_data(uint8_t *data, const char *p)
4921{
4922 int c, len, v;
4923
4924 len = 0;
4925 v = 1;
4926 for (;;) {
4927 p += strspn(p, SPACE_CHARS);
4928 if (*p == '\0')
4929 break;
4930 c = av_toupper((unsigned char) *p++);
4931 if (c >= '0' && c <= '9')
4932 c = c - '0';
4933 else if (c >= 'A' && c <= 'F')
4934 c = c - 'A' + 10;
4935 else
4936 break;
4937 v = (v << 4) | c;
4938 if (v & 0x100) {
4939 if (data)
4940 data[len] = v;
4941 len++;
4942 v = 1;
4943 }
4944 }
4945 return len;
4946}

4978void ff_parse_key_value(const char *str, ff_parse_key_val_cb callback_get_buf,
4979 void *context)
4980{
4981 const char *ptr = str;
4982
4983 /* Parse key=value pairs. */
4984 for (;;) {
4985 const char *key;
4986 char *dest = NULL, *dest_end;
4987 int key_len, dest_len = 0;
4988
4989 /* Skip whitespace and potential commas. */
4990 while (*ptr && (av_isspace(*ptr) || *ptr == ','))
4991 ptr++;
4992 if (!*ptr)
4993 break;
4994
4995 key = ptr;
4996
4997 if (!(ptr = strchr(key, '=')))
4998 break;
4999 ptr++;
5000 key_len = ptr - key;
5001
5002 callback_get_buf(context, key, key_len, &dest, &dest_len);
5003 dest_end = dest + dest_len - 1;
5004
5005 if (*ptr == '\"') {
5006 ptr++;
5007 while (*ptr && *ptr != '\"') {
5008 if (*ptr == '\\') {
5009 if (!ptr[1])
5010 break;
5011 if (dest && dest < dest_end)
5012 *dest++ = ptr[1];
5013 ptr += 2;
5014 } else {
5015 if (dest && dest < dest_end)
5016 *dest++ = *ptr;
5017 ptr++;
5018 }
5019 }
5020 if (*ptr == '\"')
5021 ptr++;
5022 } else {
5023 for (; *ptr && !(av_isspace(*ptr) || *ptr == ','); ptr++)
5024 if (dest && dest < dest_end)
5025 *dest++ = *ptr;
5026 }
5027 if (dest)
5028 *dest = 0;
5029 }
5030}

5144
5145AVRational av_guess_frame_rate(AVFormatContext *format, AVStream *st, AVFrame *frame)
5146{
5147 AVRational fr = st->r_frame_rate;
5148 AVRational codec_fr = st->internal->avctx->framerate;
5149 AVRational avg_fr = st->avg_frame_rate;
5150
5151 if (avg_fr.num > 0 && avg_fr.den > 0 && fr.num > 0 && fr.den > 0 &&
5152 av_q2d(avg_fr) < 70 && av_q2d(fr) > 210) {
5153 fr = avg_fr;
5154 }
5155
5156
5157 if (st->internal->avctx->ticks_per_frame > 1) {
5158 if ( codec_fr.num > 0 && codec_fr.den > 0 &&
5159 (fr.num == 0 || av_q2d(codec_fr) < av_q2d(fr)*0.7 && fabs(1.0 - av_q2d(av_div_q(avg_fr, fr))) > 0.1))
5160 fr = codec_fr;
5161 }
5162
5163 return fr;
5164}
5165
5166/**
5167 * Matches a stream specifier (but ignores requested index).
5168 *
5169 * @param indexptr set to point to the requested stream index if there is one
5170 *
5171 * @return <0 on error
5172 * 0 if st is NOT a matching stream
5173 * >0 if st is a matching stream
5174 */
5175static int match_stream_specifier(AVFormatContext *s, AVStream *st,
5176 const char *spec, const char **indexptr, AVProgram **p)
5177{
5178 int match = 1; /* Stores if the specifier matches so far. */
5179 while (*spec) {
5180 if (*spec <= '9' && *spec >= '0') { /* opt:index */
5181 if (indexptr)
5182 *indexptr = spec;
5183 return match;
5184 } else if (*spec == 'v' || *spec == 'a' || *spec == 's' || *spec == 'd' ||
5185 *spec == 't' || *spec == 'V') { /* opt:[vasdtV] */
5186 enum AVMediaType type;
5187 int nopic = 0;
5188
5189 switch (*spec++) {
5190 case 'v': type = AVMEDIA_TYPE_VIDEO; break;
5191 case 'a': type = AVMEDIA_TYPE_AUDIO; break;
5192 case 's': type = AVMEDIA_TYPE_SUBTITLE; break;
5193 case 'd': type = AVMEDIA_TYPE_DATA; break;
5194 case 't': type = AVMEDIA_TYPE_ATTACHMENT; break;
5195 case 'V': type = AVMEDIA_TYPE_VIDEO; nopic = 1; break;
5196 default: av_assert0(0);
5197 }
5198 if (*spec && *spec++ != ':') /* If we are not at the end, then another specifier must follow. */
5199 return AVERROR(EINVAL);
5200
5201#if FF_API_LAVF_AVCTX
5202FF_DISABLE_DEPRECATION_WARNINGS
5203 if (type != st->codecpar->codec_type
5204 && (st->codecpar->codec_type != AVMEDIA_TYPE_UNKNOWN || st->codec->codec_type != type))
5205 match = 0;
5206 FF_ENABLE_DEPRECATION_WARNINGS
5207#else
5208 if (type != st->codecpar->codec_type)
5209 match = 0;
5210#endif
5211 if (nopic && (st->disposition & AV_DISPOSITION_ATTACHED_PIC))
5212 match = 0;
5213 } else if (*spec == 'p' && *(spec + 1) == ':') {
5214 int prog_id, i, j;
5215 int found = 0;
5216 char *endptr;
5217 spec += 2;
5218 prog_id = strtol(spec, &endptr, 0);
5219 /* Disallow empty id and make sure that if we are not at the end, then another specifier must follow. */
5220 if (spec == endptr || (*endptr && *endptr++ != ':'))
5221 return AVERROR(EINVAL);
5222 spec = endptr;
5223 if (match) {
5224 for (i = 0; i < s->nb_programs; i++) {
5225 if (s->programs[i]->id != prog_id)
5226 continue;
5227
5228 for (j = 0; j < s->programs[i]->nb_stream_indexes; j++) {
5229 if (st->index == s->programs[i]->stream_index[j]) {
5230 found = 1;
5231 if (p)
5232 *p = s->programs[i];
5233 i = s->nb_programs;
5234 break;
5235 }
5236 }
5237 }
5238 }
5239 if (!found)
5240 match = 0;
5241 } else if (*spec == '#' ||
5242 (*spec == 'i' && *(spec + 1) == ':')) {
5243 int stream_id;
5244 char *endptr;
5245 spec += 1 + (*spec == 'i');
5246 stream_id = strtol(spec, &endptr, 0);
5247 if (spec == endptr || *endptr) /* Disallow empty id and make sure we are at the end. */
5248 return AVERROR(EINVAL);
5249 return match && (stream_id == st->id);
5250 } else if (*spec == 'm' && *(spec + 1) == ':') {
5251 AVDictionaryEntry *tag;
5252 char *key, *val;
5253 int ret;
5254
5255 if (match) {
5256 spec += 2;
5257 val = strchr(spec, ':');
5258
5259 key = val ? av_strndup(spec, val - spec) : av_strdup(spec);
5260 if (!key)
5261 return AVERROR(ENOMEM);
5262
5263 tag = av_dict_get(st->metadata, key, NULL, 0);
5264 if (tag) {
5265 if (!val || !strcmp(tag->value, val + 1))
5266 ret = 1;
5267 else
5268 ret = 0;
5269 } else
5270 ret = 0;
5271
5272 av_freep(&key);
5273 }
5274 return match && ret;
5275 } else if (*spec == 'u' && *(spec + 1) == '\0') {
5276 AVCodecParameters *par = st->codecpar;
5277#if FF_API_LAVF_AVCTX
5278FF_DISABLE_DEPRECATION_WARNINGS
5279 AVCodecContext *codec = st->codec;
5280FF_ENABLE_DEPRECATION_WARNINGS
5281#endif
5282 int val;
5283 switch (par->codec_type) {
5284 case AVMEDIA_TYPE_AUDIO:
5285 val = par->sample_rate && par->channels;
5286#if FF_API_LAVF_AVCTX
5287 val = val || (codec->sample_rate && codec->channels);
5288#endif
5289 if (par->format == AV_SAMPLE_FMT_NONE
5290#if FF_API_LAVF_AVCTX
5291 && codec->sample_fmt == AV_SAMPLE_FMT_NONE
5292#endif
5293 )
5294 return 0;
5295 break;
5296 case AVMEDIA_TYPE_VIDEO:
5297 val = par->width && par->height;
5298#if FF_API_LAVF_AVCTX
5299 val = val || (codec->width && codec->height);
5300#endif
5301 if (par->format == AV_PIX_FMT_NONE
5302#if FF_API_LAVF_AVCTX
5303 && codec->pix_fmt == AV_PIX_FMT_NONE
5304#endif
5305 )
5306 return 0;
5307 break;
5308 case AVMEDIA_TYPE_UNKNOWN:
5309 val = 0;
5310 break;
5311 default:
5312 val = 1;
5313 break;
5314 }
5315#if FF_API_LAVF_AVCTX
5316 return match && ((par->codec_id != AV_CODEC_ID_NONE || codec->codec_id != AV_CODEC_ID_NONE) && val != 0);
5317#else
5318 return match && (par->codec_id != AV_CODEC_ID_NONE && val != 0);
5319#endif
5320 } else {
5321 return AVERROR(EINVAL);
5322 }
5323 }
5324
5325 return match;
5326}
5327
5328
5329int avformat_match_stream_specifier(AVFormatContext *s, AVStream *st,
5330 const char *spec)
5331{
5332 int ret, index;
5333 char *endptr;
5334 const char *indexptr = NULL;
5335 AVProgram *p = NULL;
5336 int nb_streams;
5337
5338 ret = match_stream_specifier(s, st, spec, &indexptr, &p);
5339 if (ret < 0)
5340 goto error;
5341
5342 if (!indexptr)
5343 return ret;
5344
5345 index = strtol(indexptr, &endptr, 0);
5346 if (*endptr) { /* We can't have anything after the requested index. */
5347 ret = AVERROR(EINVAL);
5348 goto error;
5349 }
5350
5351 /* This is not really needed but saves us a loop for simple stream index specifiers. */
5352 if (spec == indexptr)
5353 return (index == st->index);
5354
5355 /* If we requested a matching stream index, we have to ensure st is that. */
5356 nb_streams = p ? p->nb_stream_indexes : s->nb_streams;
5357 for (int i = 0; i < nb_streams && index >= 0; i++) {
5358 AVStream *candidate = p ? s->streams[p->stream_index[i]] : s->streams[i];
5359 ret = match_stream_specifier(s, candidate, spec, NULL, NULL);
5360 if (ret < 0)
5361 goto error;
5362 if (ret > 0 && index-- == 0 && st == candidate)
5363 return 1;
5364 }
5365 return 0;
5366
5367error:
5368 if (ret == AVERROR(EINVAL))
5369 av_log(s, AV_LOG_ERROR, "Invalid stream specifier: %s.\n", spec);
5370 return ret;
5371}

5507
5508uint8_t *av_stream_get_side_data(const AVStream *st,
5509 enum AVPacketSideDataType type, buffer_size_t *size)
5510{
5511 int i;
5512
5513 for (i = 0; i < st->nb_side_data; i++) {
5514 if (st->side_data[i].type == type) {
5515 if (size)
5516 *size = st->side_data[i].size;
5517 return st->side_data[i].data;
5518 }
5519 }
5520 if (size)
5521 *size = 0;
5522 return NULL;
5523}
5524
5525int av_stream_add_side_data(AVStream *st, enum AVPacketSideDataType type,
5526 uint8_t *data, size_t size)
5527{
5528 AVPacketSideData *sd, *tmp;
5529 int i;
5530
5531 for (i = 0; i < st->nb_side_data; i++) {
5532 sd = &st->side_data[i];
5533
5534 if (sd->type == type) {
5535 av_freep(&sd->data);
5536 sd->data = data;
5537 sd->size = size;
5538 return 0;
5539 }
5540 }
5541
5542 if ((unsigned)st->nb_side_data + 1 >= INT_MAX / sizeof(*st->side_data))
5543 return AVERROR(ERANGE);
5544
5545 tmp = av_realloc(st->side_data, (st->nb_side_data + 1) * sizeof(*tmp));
5546 if (!tmp) {
5547 return AVERROR(ENOMEM);
5548 }
5549
5550 st->side_data = tmp;
5551 st->nb_side_data++;
5552
5553 sd = &st->side_data[st->nb_side_data - 1];
5554 sd->type = type;
5555 sd->data = data;
5556 sd->size = size;
5557
5558 return 0;
5559}
5560
5561uint8_t *av_stream_new_side_data(AVStream *st, enum AVPacketSideDataType type,
5562 buffer_size_t size)
5563{
5564 int ret;
5565 uint8_t *data = av_malloc(size);
5566
5567 if (!data)
5568 return NULL;
5569
5570 ret = av_stream_add_side_data(st, type, data, size);
5571 if (ret < 0) {
5572 av_freep(&data);
5573 return NULL;
5574 }
5575
5576 return data;
5577}

5579int ff_stream_add_bitstream_filter(AVStream *st, const char *name, const char *args)
5580{
5581 int ret;
5582 const AVBitStreamFilter *bsf;
5583 AVBSFContext *bsfc;
5584
5585 av_assert0(!st->internal->bsfc);
5586
5587 if (!(bsf = av_bsf_get_by_name(name))) {
5588 av_log(NULL, AV_LOG_ERROR, "Unknown bitstream filter '%s'\n", name);
5589 return AVERROR_BSF_NOT_FOUND;
5590 }
5591
5592 if ((ret = av_bsf_alloc(bsf, &bsfc)) < 0)
5593 return ret;
5594
5595 bsfc->time_base_in = st->time_base;
5596 if ((ret = avcodec_parameters_copy(bsfc->par_in, st->codecpar)) < 0) {
5597 av_bsf_free(&bsfc);
5598 return ret;
5599 }
5600
5601 if (args && bsfc->filter->priv_class) {
5602 const AVOption *opt = av_opt_next(bsfc->priv_data, NULL);
5603 const char * shorthand[2] = {NULL};
5604
5605 if (opt)
5606 shorthand[0] = opt->name;
5607
5608 if ((ret = av_opt_set_from_string(bsfc->priv_data, args, shorthand, "=", ":")) < 0) {
5609 av_bsf_free(&bsfc);
5610 return ret;
5611 }
5612 }
5613
5614 if ((ret = av_bsf_init(bsfc)) < 0) {
5615 av_bsf_free(&bsfc);
5616 return ret;
5617 }
5618
5619 st->internal->bsfc = bsfc;
5620
5621 av_log(NULL, AV_LOG_VERBOSE,
5622 "Automatically inserted bitstream filter '%s'; args='%s'\n",
5623 name, args ? args : "");
5624 return 1;
5625}

5627#if FF_API_OLD_BSF
5628FF_DISABLE_DEPRECATION_WARNINGS
5629int av_apply_bitstream_filters(AVCodecContext *codec, AVPacket *pkt,
5630 AVBitStreamFilterContext *bsfc)
5631{
5632 int ret = 0;
5633 while (bsfc) {
5634 AVPacket new_pkt = *pkt;
5635 int a = av_bitstream_filter_filter(bsfc, codec, NULL,
5636 &new_pkt.data, &new_pkt.size,
5637 pkt->data, pkt->size,
5638 pkt->flags & AV_PKT_FLAG_KEY);
5639 if (a == 0 && new_pkt.size == 0 && new_pkt.side_data_elems == 0) {
5640 av_packet_unref(pkt);
5641 memset(pkt, 0, sizeof(*pkt));
5642 return 0;
5643 }
5644 if(a == 0 && new_pkt.data != pkt->data) {
5645 uint8_t *t = av_malloc(new_pkt.size + AV_INPUT_BUFFER_PADDING_SIZE); //the new should be a subset of the old so cannot overflow
5646 if (t) {
5647 memcpy(t, new_pkt.data, new_pkt.size);
5648 memset(t + new_pkt.size, 0, AV_INPUT_BUFFER_PADDING_SIZE);
5649 new_pkt.data = t;
5650 new_pkt.buf = NULL;
5651 a = 1;
5652 } else {
5653 a = AVERROR(ENOMEM);
5654 }
5655 }
5656 if (a > 0) {
5657 new_pkt.buf = av_buffer_create(new_pkt.data, new_pkt.size,
5658 av_buffer_default_free, NULL, 0);
5659 if (new_pkt.buf) {
5660 pkt->side_data = NULL;
5661 pkt->side_data_elems = 0;
5662 av_packet_unref(pkt);
5663 } else {
5664 av_freep(&new_pkt.data);
5665 a = AVERROR(ENOMEM);
5666 }
5667 }
5668 if (a < 0) {
5669 av_log(codec, AV_LOG_ERROR,
5670 "Failed to open bitstream filter %s for stream %d with codec %s",
5671 bsfc->filter->name, pkt->stream_index,
5672 codec->codec ? codec->codec->name : "copy");
5673 ret = a;
5674 break;
5675 }
5676 *pkt = new_pkt;
5677
5678 bsfc = bsfc->next;
5679 }
5680 return ret;
5681}

5708{

5733int ff_get_packet_palette(AVFormatContext *s, AVPacket *pkt, int ret, uint32_t *palette)
5734{
5735 uint8_t *side_data;
5736 buffer_size_t size;
5737
5738 side_data = av_packet_get_side_data(pkt, AV_PKT_DATA_PALETTE, &size);
5739 if (side_data) {
5740 if (size != AVPALETTE_SIZE) {
5741 av_log(s, AV_LOG_ERROR, "Invalid palette side data\n");
5742 return AVERROR_INVALIDDATA;
5743 }
5744 memcpy(palette, side_data, AVPALETTE_SIZE);
5745 return 1;
5746 }
5747
5748 if (ret == CONTAINS_PAL) {
5749 int i;
5750 for (i = 0; i < AVPALETTE_COUNT; i++)
5751 palette[i] = AV_RL32(pkt->data + pkt->size - AVPALETTE_SIZE + i*4);
5752 return 1;
5753 }
5754
5755 return 0;
5756}

5758int ff_bprint_to_codecpar_extradata(AVCodecParameters *par, struct AVBPrint *buf)
5759{
5760 int ret;
5761 char *str;
5762
5763 ret = av_bprint_finalize(buf, &str);
5764 if (ret < 0)
5765 return ret;
5766 if (!av_bprint_is_complete(buf)) {
5767 av_free(str);

5769 }
5770
5771 par->extradata = str;
5772 /* Note: the string is NUL terminated (so extradata can be read as a
5773 * string), but the ending character is not accounted in the size (in
5774 * binary formats you are likely not supposed to mux that character). When
5775 * extradata is copied, it is also padded with AV_INPUT_BUFFER_PADDING_SIZE
5776 * zeros. */
5777 par->extradata_size = buf->len;
5778 return 0;
5779}
5780
5781int avformat_transfer_internal_stream_timing_info(const AVOutputFormat *ofmt,
5782 AVStream *ost, const AVStream *ist,
5783 enum AVTimebaseSource copy_tb)
5784{
5785 //TODO: use [io]st->internal->avctx
5786 const AVCodecContext *dec_ctx;
5787 AVCodecContext *enc_ctx;
5788
5789#if FF_API_LAVF_AVCTX
5790FF_DISABLE_DEPRECATION_WARNINGS
5791 dec_ctx = ist->codec;
5792 enc_ctx = ost->codec;
5793FF_ENABLE_DEPRECATION_WARNINGS
5794#else
5795 dec_ctx = ist->internal->avctx;
5796 enc_ctx = ost->internal->avctx;
5797#endif
5798
5799 enc_ctx->time_base = ist->time_base;
5800 /*
5801 * Avi is a special case here because it supports variable fps but
5802 * having the fps and timebase differe significantly adds quite some
5803 * overhead
5804 */
5805 if (!strcmp(ofmt->name, "avi")) {
5806#if FF_API_R_FRAME_RATE
5807 if (copy_tb == AVFMT_TBCF_AUTO && ist->r_frame_rate.num
5808 && av_q2d(ist->r_frame_rate) >= av_q2d(ist->avg_frame_rate)
5809 && 0.5/av_q2d(ist->r_frame_rate) > av_q2d(ist->time_base)
5810 && 0.5/av_q2d(ist->r_frame_rate) > av_q2d(dec_ctx->time_base)
5811 && av_q2d(ist->time_base) < 1.0/500 && av_q2d(dec_ctx->time_base) < 1.0/500
5812 || copy_tb == AVFMT_TBCF_R_FRAMERATE) {
5813 enc_ctx->time_base.num = ist->r_frame_rate.den;
5814 enc_ctx->time_base.den = 2*ist->r_frame_rate.num;
5815 enc_ctx->ticks_per_frame = 2;
5816 } else
5817#endif
5818 if (copy_tb == AVFMT_TBCF_AUTO && av_q2d(dec_ctx->time_base)*dec_ctx->ticks_per_frame > 2*av_q2d(ist->time_base)
5819 && av_q2d(ist->time_base) < 1.0/500
5820 || copy_tb == AVFMT_TBCF_DECODER) {
5821 enc_ctx->time_base = dec_ctx->time_base;
5822 enc_ctx->time_base.num *= dec_ctx->ticks_per_frame;
5823 enc_ctx->time_base.den *= 2;
5824 enc_ctx->ticks_per_frame = 2;
5825 }
5826 } else if (!(ofmt->flags & AVFMT_VARIABLE_FPS)
5827 && !av_match_name(ofmt->name, "mov,mp4,3gp,3g2,psp,ipod,ismv,f4v")) {
5828 if (copy_tb == AVFMT_TBCF_AUTO && dec_ctx->time_base.den
5829 && av_q2d(dec_ctx->time_base)*dec_ctx->ticks_per_frame > av_q2d(ist->time_base)
5830 && av_q2d(ist->time_base) < 1.0/500
5831 || copy_tb == AVFMT_TBCF_DECODER) {
5832 enc_ctx->time_base = dec_ctx->time_base;
5833 enc_ctx->time_base.num *= dec_ctx->ticks_per_frame;
5834 }
5835 }
5836
5837 if ((enc_ctx->codec_tag == AV_RL32("tmcd") || ost->codecpar->codec_tag == AV_RL32("tmcd"))
5838 && dec_ctx->time_base.num < dec_ctx->time_base.den
5839 && dec_ctx->time_base.num > 0
5840 && 121LL*dec_ctx->time_base.num > dec_ctx->time_base.den) {
5841 enc_ctx->time_base = dec_ctx->time_base;
5842 }
5843
5844 if (ost->avg_frame_rate.num)
5845 enc_ctx->time_base = av_inv_q(ost->avg_frame_rate);
5846
5847 av_reduce(&enc_ctx->time_base.num, &enc_ctx->time_base.den,
5848 enc_ctx->time_base.num, enc_ctx->time_base.den, INT_MAX);
5849
5850 return 0;
5851}
